<!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
<meta http-equiv="x-ua-compatible" content="IE=edge">
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
<title>MFTECmd Wrapper</title>
<HTA:APPLICATION
  ID="mftHta"
  APPLICATIONNAME="MFTECmd Wrapper"
  BORDER="thick"
  CAPTION="yes"
  SCROLL="auto"
  SINGLEINSTANCE="yes"
  SHOWINTASKBAR="yes"
  MAXIMIZEBUTTON="yes"
  MINIMIZEBUTTON="yes"
  INNERBORDER="no"
  CONTEXTMENU="yes"
  SELECTION="yes" />
<!--
  MFTECmd Wrapper - hybrid launcher (spec Artifacts/MFTECmd-MFT/SPEC.md).
  This .hta is a THIN LAUNCHER only: it renders a form, extracts the embedded
  MFTECmd-Engine.ps1 next to itself at run time, invokes it, tails its log, and
  opens the self-contained HTML report in Edge. It never loads MFT/USN row data
  itself (that is 0.5-2M rows - far past what mshta can hold). All heavy lifting
  is in the PS1; all rendering is in the emitted report, viewed in Chromium.

  MFTECmd contract (verified 2026-07-03 against v1.2.2.1):
    - $MFT:  MFTECmd.exe -f "<$MFT>" --csv "<out>" --csvf mft.csv
    - $J:    MFTECmd.exe -f "<$J>" -m "<$MFT>" --csv "<out>" --csvf j.csv   (-m resolves ParentPath)
    - Needs a real console (Console.WindowWidth) -> always run via a cmd window.
    - On a cmd command line the %3A in Velociraptor paths must stay SINGLE; the
      %-doubling batEsc() is for the .bat FILE lines the engine is NOT written into.
      Here we pass paths as PS -File arguments, so batEsc applies only to the bat
      wrapper line, and the engine receives clean single-% paths. (verified)
  Payload trap: the embedded PS1 is stored in a <script type="text/plain"> block.
  The engine is written so NO literal close-script sequence appears in it (it builds
  that tag by concatenation), so the block cannot be terminated early. A startup
  self-check confirms the payload ends with '# MFTECMD-ENGINE-END'.
-->
<style>
  html{margin:0;height:100%;background:#0d1117}
  body{margin:0;height:100%;background:#0d1117;color:#e6edf3;font-family:Segoe UI,Tahoma,sans-serif;font-size:16px}
  #content{zoom:0.9}
  .modal{position:fixed;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;background:rgba(0,0,0,.66);z-index:1000;overflow:auto}
  .modal .mcard{max-width:780px;margin:36px auto;background:#161b22;border:1px solid #30363d;border-radius:10px;padding:18px 22px}
  .modal h2{margin:0 0 6px;font-size:18px;font-weight:600}
  .modal h3{margin:12px 0 4px;font-size:12px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;color:#8b949e}
  .modal ul{margin:4px 0;padding-left:20px}.modal li{margin:3px 0;font-size:13px}
  .modal p{font-size:13px;margin:6px 0}
  .modal code{background:#0d1117;border:1px solid #30363d;border-radius:4px;padding:2px 6px;font-family:Consolas,monospace;font-size:12px}
  .modal .x{float:right;cursor:pointer;color:#8b949e;font-size:22px;line-height:1}.modal .x:hover{color:#e6edf3}
  .modal .gh{font-family:Consolas,monospace;font-size:12px}
  a{color:#58a6ff}
  .mono{font-family:Consolas,"Courier New",monospace}
  .muted{color:#8b949e}
  .err{color:#f85149}
  .ok{color:#3fb950}
  header{padding:8px 14px;background:#161b22;border-bottom:1px solid #30363d}
  header h1{display:inline-block;font-size:15px;margin:0;font-weight:600;vertical-align:middle}
  header h1 small{color:#8b949e;font-weight:400}
  .pill{display:inline-block;font-size:11px;color:#8b949e;border:1px solid #30363d;border-radius:20px;padding:2px 10px;margin-left:8px;vertical-align:middle}
  .wrap{padding:12px 14px}
  .card{background:#161b22;border:1px solid #30363d;border-radius:8px;padding:12px;margin-bottom:12px}
  .card h3{margin:0 0 8px;font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;color:#8b949e}
  label.fld{display:block;margin:8px 0 2px;font-size:11px;color:#8b949e}
  input.txt,select,textarea{background:#1c2330;border:1px solid #30363d;color:#e6edf3;border-radius:6px;padding:5px 8px;font-size:13px;font-family:Consolas,monospace}
  input.wide{width:70%}
  input.mid{width:38%}
  textarea.ioc{width:70%;height:64px;white-space:pre;overflow:auto}
  .btn{background:#1c2330;border:1px solid #30363d;color:#e6edf3;border-radius:6px;padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;cursor:pointer;margin:2px}
  .btn:hover{border-color:#58a6ff}
  .btn.primary{background:#1f6feb;border-color:#1f6feb}
  .btn:disabled{opacity:.5;cursor:default;border-color:#30363d}
  .row{white-space:nowrap;margin:2px 0}
  .hint{font-size:11px;color:#8b949e;margin-top:3px}
  .sep{display:inline-block;width:1px;height:18px;background:#30363d;margin:0 6px;vertical-align:middle}
  #status{margin:6px 0;font-size:12px}
  #exeline{font-size:11px;color:#8b949e;margin-top:6px}
  #log{white-space:pre-wrap;font-family:Consolas,monospace;font-size:11px;color:#8b949e;max-height:280px;overflow:auto;background:#0d1117;border:1px solid #30363d;border-radius:6px;padding:8px;display:none;margin-top:8px}
  .hide{display:none}
  .grid2{display:inline-block;width:49%;vertical-align:top}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<header>
  <h1>MFTECmd Wrapper <small>&mdash; $MFT / $J filesystem triage <span id="appver"></span></small></h1>
  <span class="pill" id="verpill">version: checking&hellip;</span>
  <span class="pill" id="modepill">launcher</span>
  <span style="float:right">
    <button class="btn" id="helpBtn" onclick="openHelp()" title="Help, about &amp; GitHub link">Help</button>
    <button class="btn" id="fdown" title="Smaller text">A&minus;</button>
    <button class="btn" id="fup" title="Larger text">A+</button>
  </span>
</header>

<div class="wrap" id="content">

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Input artifacts</h3>
    <div class="row">
      <label class="fld">$MFT file (required)</label>
      <input class="txt wide mono" id="mftPath" placeholder="path to a collected $MFT (e.g. ...\uploads\ntfs\%5C%5C.%5CC%3A\$MFT)">
      <button class="btn" id="mftBrowse">Browse file&hellip;</button>
      <button class="btn" id="mftDirBrowse">Browse collection&hellip;</button>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <label class="fld">$J USN journal (optional, strongly recommended)</label>
      <input class="txt wide mono" id="jPath" placeholder="path to $Extend\$UsnJrnl%3A$J - auto-filled when found next to $MFT">
      <button class="btn" id="jBrowse">Browse file&hellip;</button>
      <button class="btn" id="jClear">Clear</button>
    </div>
    <div id="exeline"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Options</h3>
    <div class="row">
      <span class="grid2">
        <label class="fld">Host label (report name + header)</label>
        <input class="txt mono" style="width:80%" id="hostLabel" placeholder="auto-detected from collection folder">
      </span>
      <span class="grid2">
        <label class="fld">Embedded row budget (per set)</label>
        <select id="rowBudget">
          <option value="50000">50,000</option>
          <option value="100000" selected>100,000 (default)</option>
          <option value="200000">200,000</option>
        </select>
      </span>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <span class="grid2">
        <label class="fld">Window from (UTC, YYYY-MM-DD, optional)</label>
        <input class="txt mono" style="width:60%" id="winFrom" placeholder="2026-06-01">
      </span>
      <span class="grid2">
        <label class="fld">Window to (UTC, YYYY-MM-DD, optional)</label>
        <input class="txt mono" style="width:60%" id="winTo" placeholder="2026-06-30">
      </span>
    </div>
    <div class="hint">The window is not a hard filter - it prioritises in-window rows during reduction and drives the ACTIVE-window heuristics.</div>
    <div class="row">
      <label class="fld">IOC terms (optional, comma or newline separated) - baked in at parse time so hits always survive reduction</label>
      <textarea class="ioc mono" id="iocBox" placeholder="one term per line, e.g.&#10;\AppData\Local\Temp\&#10;payload.exe&#10;suspicious.dll&#10;&hellip;"></textarea>
      <button class="btn" id="iocLoad">Load from file&hellip;</button>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <label class="fld">Output folder (report + full CSVs land here)</label>
      <input class="txt wide mono" id="outDir">
      <button class="btn" id="outBrowse">Browse&hellip;</button>
      <button class="btn" id="outOpen">Open</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="row">
      <button class="btn primary" id="runBtn">Process &rarr; build report</button>
      <button class="btn" id="viewBtn" disabled>View last report</button>
      <span class="sep"></span>
      <button class="btn" id="verBtn">Check MFTECmd version</button>
      <button class="btn" id="updBtn">Update / download MFTECmd</button>
      <span class="sep"></span>
      <button class="btn" id="logToggle">Show log</button>
    </div>
    <div id="status" class="muted">Ready.</div>
    <div id="log" data-ph="1"></div>
  </div>

</div>

<!-- ============================ EMBEDDED PS1 PAYLOAD ============================
     The full MFTECmd-Engine.ps1 is injected verbatim between the markers below by
     the build/splice step. It is inert here (type="text/plain"); the launcher reads
     it back with getElementById("ps1Payload").text and writes it to disk at run time.
     Do NOT hand-edit inside the markers - edit MFTECmd-Engine.ps1 and re-splice. -->
<script type="text/plain" id="ps1Payload">
# MFTECmd-Engine.ps1 - parse/score/reduce/report engine for MFTECmd-Wrapper.
# Phase 1: standalone script (later embedded in MFTECmd-Wrapper.hta).
# Target: Windows PowerShell 5.1. ASCII only. All timestamps UTC, never localized.
# Contract: exit 0 and print report path on the LAST line; nonzero + message on error.
# MFTECMD-ENGINE-START
param(
    [Parameter(Mandatory=$true)][string]$Mft,
    [string]$J = "",
    [Parameter(Mandatory=$true)][string]$OutDir,
    [string]$HostLabel = "",
    [string]$IocFile = "",
    [int]$RowBudget = 100000,
    [string]$From = "",
    [string]$To = "",
    [string]$AppVersion = "0.1.0-dev",
    [string]$MftecmdPath = ""
)

$ErrorActionPreference = "Stop"
$sw = [System.Diagnostics.Stopwatch]::StartNew()

function Say([string]$m) {
    Write-Output ("[{0}] {1}" -f $sw.Elapsed.ToString("mm\:ss"), $m)
}
function Fail([string]$m) {
    Write-Output ("ERROR: " + $m)
    exit 1
}

# ---------------------------------------------------------------- constants
# NB: PS variable names are case-insensitive - constants here must never share a
# name with per-row locals (a '$risky = ...' assignment would clobber '$RISKY').
$RISKYEXT = @{}
foreach ($e in @("exe","dll","sys","ps1","psm1","bat","cmd","vbs","vbe","js","jse",
                 "wsf","hta","jar","msi","scr","cpl","lnk","iso","img","vhd","vhdx",
                 "7z","zip","rar")) { $RISKYEXT[$e] = $true }

# user-writable path fragments (lowercase, matched against lowercase full path)
$USERPATHS = @("\users\","\appdata\","\temp\","\downloads\","\programdata\",
               "\perflogs\","\windows\temp\","\`$recycle.bin\","\public\",
               "\config\systemprofile\")
# paths that LOOK user-writable by fragment but are not (servicing noise)
$NOTUSERPATHS = @("\winsxs\","\windows\servicing\","\windows\softwaredistribution\")

$LOLBINS = @{}
foreach ($e in @("powershell","powershell_ise","pwsh","cmd","wscript","cscript",
                 "mshta","rundll32","regsvr32","certutil","certreq","bitsadmin",
                 "msiexec","curl","wget","node","java","javaw","python","pythonw",
                 "php","autoit3","nc","ncat","psexec","psexesvc","wmic","schtasks",
                 "reg","sc")) { $LOLBINS[$e] = $true }

$OSNAMES = @{}
foreach ($e in @("svchost","lsass","csrss","services","winlogon","explorer",
                 "taskhostw","dllhost","conhost","smss","wininit")) { $OSNAMES[$e] = $true }

# deceptive naming: doc-looking name with executable payload extension, or a
# DIRECTORY named like a document (a loader pattern seen in the wild: a folder
# named e.g. report.docx that actually holds an executable payload)
$reDblExt = [regex]::new('\.(doc|docx|pdf|xls|xlsx|ppt|pptx|txt|rtf|csv|jpg|jpeg|png)\.(exe|scr|com|bat|cmd|js|jse|vbs|vbe|hta|ps1|lnk)$',
    [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::IgnoreCase -bor [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Compiled)
$reDocDir = [regex]::new('\.(doc|docx|pdf|xls|xlsx|ppt|pptx)$',
    [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::IgnoreCase -bor [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Compiled)
# JSON escape trigger: anything outside plain printable ASCII, or " \ <
$reJsonEsc = [regex]::new('[^\x20-\x7E]|["\\<]',
    [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Compiled)

$RECENT_DAYS = 14
$CRTDEL_HOURS = 48
$BURST_N = 50
$BURST_SECS = 600

# ---------------------------------------------------------------- helpers
function LooksRandom([string]$base) {
    # conservative on purpose: 'comctl32' / 'mfmpeg2srcsnk' style system names must
    # not fire; hex/base32-looking payload names should
    if ($base.Length -lt 10) { return $false }
    $v = 0; $d = 0
    for ($i = 0; $i -lt $base.Length; $i++) {
        $c = $base[$i]
        if ("aeiouy".IndexOf($c) -ge 0) { $v++ }
        elseif ($c -ge '0' -and $c -le '9') { $d++ }
        elseif (-not ($c -ge 'a' -and $c -le 'z')) { return $false } # only [a-z0-9] qualifies
    }
    $vr = $v / $base.Length
    if ($vr -lt 0.1 -and ($d -ge 2 -or $base.Length -ge 16)) { return $true }
    return $false
}

# split one physical CSV line; caller guarantees quotes are balanced
function SplitCsvLine([string]$line) {
    if ($line.IndexOf('"') -lt 0) { return $line.Split(',') }
    $out = New-Object System.Collections.Generic.List[string]
    $sb = New-Object System.Text.StringBuilder
    $inQ = $false
    for ($i = 0; $i -lt $line.Length; $i++) {
        $c = $line[$i]
        if ($inQ) {
            if ($c -eq '"') {
                if ($i + 1 -lt $line.Length -and $line[$i+1] -eq '"') { [void]$sb.Append('"'); $i++ }
                else { $inQ = $false }
            } else { [void]$sb.Append($c) }
        } else {
            if ($c -eq '"') { $inQ = $true }
            elseif ($c -eq ',') { $out.Add($sb.ToString()); [void]$sb.Clear() }
            else { [void]$sb.Append($c) }
        }
    }
    $out.Add($sb.ToString())
    return $out.ToArray()
}

# read one logical CSV record (merges physical lines while quotes are unbalanced)
function ReadCsvRecord([System.IO.StreamReader]$sr) {
    $line = $sr.ReadLine()
    if ($null -eq $line) { return $null }
    if ($line.IndexOf('"') -ge 0) {
        $qc = $line.Length - $line.Replace('"','').Length
        while (($qc % 2) -eq 1) {
            $nxt = $sr.ReadLine()
            if ($null -eq $nxt) { break }
            $line = $line + "`n" + $nxt
            $qc += $nxt.Length - $nxt.Replace('"','').Length
        }
    }
    return $line
}

function JsonStr([string]$s, [System.Text.StringBuilder]$sb) {
    [void]$sb.Append('"')
    if ($null -ne $s -and $s.Length -gt 0) {
        if (-not $reJsonEsc.IsMatch($s)) {
            [void]$sb.Append($s)
        } else {
            for ($i = 0; $i -lt $s.Length; $i++) {
                $c = $s[$i]
                switch ($c) {
                    '"'  { [void]$sb.Append('\"') }
                    '\'  { [void]$sb.Append('\\') }
                    '<'  { [void]$sb.Append('\u').Append('003C') }  # so data can never form a close-script tag
                    "`n" { [void]$sb.Append('\n') }
                    "`r" { [void]$sb.Append('\r') }
                    "`t" { [void]$sb.Append('\t') }
                    default {
                        $n = [int]$c
                        if ($n -lt 32 -or $n -gt 126) { [void]$sb.Append('\u').Append($n.ToString('X4')) }
                        else { [void]$sb.Append($c) }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    [void]$sb.Append('"')
}

function ColIx([hashtable]$map, [string]$name) {
    if (-not $map.ContainsKey($name)) { Fail ("CSV is missing expected column '" + $name + "' - MFTECmd version mismatch?") }
    return [int]$map[$name]
}

# ---------------------------------------------------------------- stage 0: inputs
if (-not (Test-Path -LiteralPath $Mft)) { Fail ("`$MFT not found: " + $Mft) }
$haveJ = ($J -ne "" -and (Test-Path -LiteralPath $J))
if ($J -ne "" -and -not $haveJ) { Say ("WARN: `$J path not found, continuing MFT-only: " + $J) }
if (-not (Test-Path -LiteralPath $OutDir)) { New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path $OutDir | Out-Null }
$csvDir = Join-Path $OutDir "csv"
if (-not (Test-Path -LiteralPath $csvDir)) { New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path $csvDir | Out-Null }

if ($HostLabel -eq "") {
    if ($Mft -match 'Collection-([A-Za-z0-9\-_]+?)-\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}') { $HostLabel = $Matches[1] }
    else { $HostLabel = "HOST" }
}
$safeHost = ($HostLabel -replace '[^A-Za-z0-9\-_\.]', '_')

# IOC list: comma/newline separated, lowercased, '#' comments ignored
$IOCS = @()
if ($IocFile -ne "" -and (Test-Path -LiteralPath $IocFile)) {
    $raw = [System.IO.File]::ReadAllText($IocFile)
    $IOCS = @($raw -split '[,\r\n]+' | ForEach-Object { $_.Trim().ToLowerInvariant() } |
              Where-Object { $_ -ne "" -and -not $_.StartsWith("#") } | Select-Object -Unique)
}
$nIoc = $IOCS.Count

# normalize window bounds to sortable 'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss' strings
$winFrom = ""; $winTo = ""
if ($From -ne "") { $winFrom = ($From.Trim() + " 00:00:00").Substring(0,19) }
if ($To -ne "")   { $winTo   = ($To.Trim()   + " 23:59:59").Substring(0,19) }
$haveWin = ($winFrom -ne "" -or $winTo -ne "")

Say ("Engine v" + $AppVersion + "  host=" + $HostLabel + "  iocs=" + $nIoc + "  budget=" + $RowBudget + "/set")

# ---------------------------------------------------------------- stage 1: run MFTECmd
if ($MftecmdPath -eq "") {
    $cand = @(
        (Join-Path (Split-Path -Parent $MyInvocation.MyCommand.Path) "MFTECmd.exe"),
        "C:\Users\Forensics\Downloads\1-Package\KAPE\Modules\bin\MFTECmd.exe",
        "C:\Tools\net9\MFTECmd.exe"
    )
    foreach ($c in $cand) { if (Test-Path -LiteralPath $c) { $MftecmdPath = $c; break } }
}
if ($MftecmdPath -eq "" -or -not (Test-Path -LiteralPath $MftecmdPath)) { Fail "MFTECmd.exe not found (searched script dir, KAPE bin, C:\Tools\net9)" }
$toolVer = (Get-Item -LiteralPath $MftecmdPath).VersionInfo.FileVersion

$mftCsv = Join-Path $csvDir "mft.csv"
$jCsv   = Join-Path $csvDir "j.csv"
$env:DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD = "Major"

function RunTool([string]$args_, [string]$logName) {
    $log = Join-Path $csvDir $logName
    # NB: cmd /c command line - do NOT double % here (that is batch-FILE escaping).
    # MFTECmd probes the console; the HTA launcher always provides one.
    cmd /c ("`"" + $MftecmdPath + "`" " + $args_ + " > `"" + $log + "`" 2>&1")
    return $LASTEXITCODE
}

if ((Test-Path -LiteralPath $mftCsv) -and ((Get-Item -LiteralPath $mftCsv).Length -gt 0)) {
    Say ("[1/6] Reusing existing " + $mftCsv)
} else {
    Say "[1/6] Running MFTECmd on `$MFT ..."
    $rc = RunTool ("-f `"" + $Mft + "`" --csv `"" + $csvDir + "`" --csvf mft.csv") "mftecmd_mft.log"
    if ($rc -ne 0 -or -not (Test-Path -LiteralPath $mftCsv)) { Fail ("MFTECmd `$MFT parse failed (rc=" + $rc + ") - see " + (Join-Path $csvDir "mftecmd_mft.log")) }
}
if ($haveJ) {
    if ((Test-Path -LiteralPath $jCsv) -and ((Get-Item -LiteralPath $jCsv).Length -gt 0)) {
        Say ("[1/6] Reusing existing " + $jCsv)
    } else {
        Say "[1/6] Running MFTECmd on `$J ..."
        $rc = RunTool ("-f `"" + $J + "`" -m `"" + $Mft + "`" --csv `"" + $csvDir + "`" --csvf j.csv") "mftecmd_j.log"
        if ($rc -ne 0 -or -not (Test-Path -LiteralPath $jCsv)) { Fail ("MFTECmd `$J parse failed (rc=" + $rc + ") - see " + (Join-Path $csvDir "mftecmd_j.log")) }
    }
}

# ---------------------------------------------------------------- stage 2: parse + score $MFT
# kept-row layout (indexes matter - viewer cols map below must match):
#  0 entry 1 seq 2 deleted 3 parentPath 4 fileName 5 ext 6 size 7 isDir 8 hasAds
#  9 zoneId 10 cr10 11 cr30 12 mod10 13 acc10 14 score 15 tags 16 why
Say "[2/6] Parsing + scoring `$MFT csv ..."

$t1m = New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]'   # IOC hits
$t2m = New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]'   # score >= 4
$t3m = New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]'   # score >= 2
$t4m = New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]'   # score >= 1
$t5m = New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]'   # in-window risky ext
$t6m = New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]'   # remainder (bounded, newest kept)
$t6mMin = ""      # newest-N threshold: skip rows older than this once bounded
$mftTotal = 0; $mftDel = 0; $mftAds = 0; $mftStomp = 0; $mftIoc = 0
$maxTsM = ""

$srm = New-Object System.IO.StreamReader($mftCsv, [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8, $true, 1MB)
try {
    $hdr = $srm.ReadLine()
    if ($hdr.Length -gt 0 -and [int]$hdr[0] -eq 0xFEFF) { $hdr = $hdr.Substring(1) }
    $map = @{}; $hc = $hdr.Split(','); for ($i = 0; $i -lt $hc.Length; $i++) { $map[$hc[$i]] = $i }
    $cEntry = ColIx $map "EntryNumber";  $cSeq = ColIx $map "SequenceNumber"
    $cInUse = ColIx $map "InUse";        $cPP  = ColIx $map "ParentPath"
    $cFN    = ColIx $map "FileName";     $cExt = ColIx $map "Extension"
    $cSize  = ColIx $map "FileSize";     $cDir = ColIx $map "IsDirectory"
    $cAds   = ColIx $map "HasAds";       $cIsAds = ColIx $map "IsAds"
    $cSiFn  = ColIx $map "SI<FN";        $cZone  = ColIx $map "ZoneIdContents"
    $cCr10  = ColIx $map "Created0x10";  $cCr30  = ColIx $map "Created0x30"
    $cMod10 = ColIx $map "LastModified0x10"; $cAcc10 = ColIx $map "LastAccess0x10"
    $nCols = $hc.Length

    while ($true) {
        $line = ReadCsvRecord $srm
        if ($null -eq $line) { break }
        if ($line.Length -eq 0) { continue }
        $f = SplitCsvLine $line
        if ($f.Length -lt $nCols) { continue }   # malformed tail row
        $mftTotal++

        $fn  = $f[$cFN];  $pp = $f[$cPP]
        $ext = $f[$cExt]; if ($ext.Length -gt 0 -and $ext[0] -eq '.') { $ext = $ext.Substring(1) }
        $extL = $ext.ToLowerInvariant()
        $isDir = ($f[$cDir] -eq "True")
        $deleted = ($f[$cInUse] -ne "True")
        $hasAds = ($f[$cAds] -eq "True")
        $zone = $f[$cZone]
        $cr10 = $f[$cCr10]; $cr30 = $f[$cCr30]; $mod10 = $f[$cMod10]
        if ($deleted) { $mftDel++ }
        if ($hasAds) { $mftAds++ }
        if ($cr10.CompareTo($maxTsM) -gt 0) { $maxTsM = $cr10 }

        $risky = ($extL.Length -gt 0 -and $RISKYEXT.ContainsKey($extL))
        $score = 0; $tags = ""; $why = ""
        $fpL = $null
        if ($nIoc -gt 0 -or $risky -or $extL -eq "exe" -or ($isDir -and $fn.IndexOf('.') -ge 0)) {
            $fpL = ($pp + "\" + $fn).ToLowerInvariant()
        }

        $inUser = $false
        if ($null -ne $fpL) {
            foreach ($u in $USERPATHS) { if ($fpL.IndexOf($u) -ge 0) { $inUser = $true; break } }
            if ($inUser) {
                foreach ($u in $NOTUSERPATHS) { if ($fpL.IndexOf($u) -ge 0) { $inUser = $false; break } }
            }
        }

        # H1 USERPATH
        if ($risky -and $inUser) { $score += 2; $tags += "|USERPATH"; $why += "; risky ext in user-writable path" }
        # H2 TIMESTOMP (MFTECmd SI<FN flag; ignore sub-second-only deltas; files only)
        if (-not $isDir -and $f[$cSiFn] -eq "True" -and $cr30.Length -ge 19 -and $cr10.Length -ge 19 -and
            $cr30.Substring(0,19) -ne $cr10.Substring(0,19)) {
            $mftStomp++
            # +3 only for executable content in user paths; installers and cloud-sync
            # clients (Dropbox/OneDrive preserve old SI times) make this noisy otherwise.
            # Downloaded files (Zone.Identifier present) are the #1 benign SI<FN source -
            # download+extract keeps original timestamps - so demote them to +1 even when
            # risky+userpath, which is exactly a downloaded installer .dll/.exe. (Verified:
            # 2017 Dell / 2021 SciWord installer packages were out-ranking the RAT otherwise.)
            if ($inUser -and $risky -and $zone.Length -eq 0) { $score += 3 } else { $score += 1 }
            $tags += "|TIMESTOMP"; $why += "; SI created (" + $cr10.Substring(0,19) + ") earlier than FN created (" + $cr30.Substring(0,19) + ")"
        }
        # H3 ADS
        if ($hasAds -and -not $isDir) {
            $score += 1; $tags += "|ADS"
            if ($zone.Length -gt 0) { $score += 1; $why += "; downloaded (Zone.Identifier present)" } else { $why += "; has alternate data stream" }
        }
        # H5 MASQ
        if ($extL -eq "exe") {
            $base = $fn.Substring(0, $fn.Length - 4).ToLowerInvariant()
            if ($OSNAMES.ContainsKey($base) -and $fpL.IndexOf("\windows\") -lt 0) {
                $score += 3; $tags += "|MASQ"; $why += "; OS binary name outside \Windows"
            }
        }
        # H6 RANDOM
        if ($risky) {
            $dot = $fn.LastIndexOf('.')
            $base = if ($dot -gt 0) { $fn.Substring(0, $dot).ToLowerInvariant() } else { $fn.ToLowerInvariant() }
            if (LooksRandom $base) { $score += 1; $tags += "|RANDOM"; $why += "; random-looking name" }
        }
        # H7 DBLEXT (file: doc.pdf.exe / dir named like a document)
        if ($risky -and $reDblExt.IsMatch($fn)) {
            $score += 2; $tags += "|DBLEXT"; $why += "; double extension"
        } elseif ($isDir -and $fn.IndexOf('.') -ge 0 -and $reDocDir.IsMatch($fn)) {
            $score += 2; $tags += "|DBLEXT"; $why += "; DIRECTORY named like a document"
        }
        # H9 DELEXE
        if ($deleted -and $risky) { $score += 1; $tags += "|DELETED"; $why += "; deleted" }
        # H10 IOC
        $iocHit = $false
        if ($nIoc -gt 0) {
            $hits = ""
            foreach ($t in $IOCS) {
                if ($fpL.IndexOf($t) -ge 0 -or ($zone.Length -gt 0 -and $zone.ToLowerInvariant().IndexOf($t) -ge 0)) {
                    if ($hits -ne "") { $hits += ", " }
                    $hits += $t
                    if ($hits.Length -gt 120) { break }
                }
            }
            # IOC = analyst-supplied known-bad. Weight it so a hit outranks any stack of
            # generic heuristics (a benign old installer can reach USERPATH+TIMESTOMP+ADS=6;
            # a real indicator match must sit above that). +5 puts USERPATH+IOC at 7.
            if ($hits -ne "") { $iocHit = $true; $mftIoc++; $score += 5; $tags += "|IOC"; $why += "; IOC hit: " + $hits }
        }

        # size/entry as numbers for compact JSON
        $sizeN = [long]0; [void][long]::TryParse($f[$cSize], [ref]$sizeN)
        $entN = 0; [void][int]::TryParse($f[$cEntry], [ref]$entN)
        $seqN = 0; [void][int]::TryParse($f[$cSeq], [ref]$seqN)
        $row = @($entN, $seqN, $(if ($deleted) {1} else {0}), $pp, $fn, $extL, $sizeN,
                 $(if ($isDir) {1} else {0}), $(if ($hasAds) {1} else {0}), $zone,
                 $(if ($cr10.Length -ge 19) { $cr10.Substring(0,19) } else { $cr10 }),
                 $(if ($cr30.Length -ge 19) { $cr30.Substring(0,19) } else { $cr30 }),
                 $(if ($mod10.Length -ge 19) { $mod10.Substring(0,19) } else { $mod10 }),
                 $(if ($f[$cAcc10].Length -ge 19) { $f[$cAcc10].Substring(0,19) } else { $f[$cAcc10] }),
                 $score, $tags.TrimStart('|'), $why.TrimStart('; '))

        if ($iocHit) { $t1m.Add($row) }
        elseif ($score -ge 4) { $t2m.Add($row) }
        elseif ($score -ge 2) { $t3m.Add($row) }
        elseif ($score -ge 1) { $t4m.Add($row) }
        else {
            $ts = [string]$row[10]
            $inWin = $false
            if ($haveWin) {
                $inWin = $true
                if ($winFrom -ne "" -and $ts.CompareTo($winFrom) -lt 0) { $inWin = $false }
                if ($winTo -ne "" -and $ts.CompareTo($winTo) -gt 0) { $inWin = $false }
            }
            if ($inWin -and $risky) { $t5m.Add($row) }
            else {
                # bounded newest-N remainder
                if ($t6mMin -eq "" -or $ts.CompareTo($t6mMin) -ge 0) {
                    $t6m.Add($row)
                    if ($t6m.Count -ge ($RowBudget * 2)) {
                        $keys = New-Object 'string[]' $t6m.Count
                        $items = $t6m.ToArray()
                        for ($k = 0; $k -lt $items.Length; $k++) { $keys[$k] = [string]$items[$k][10] }
                        [System.Array]::Sort($keys, $items)          # ascending; newest at end
                        $t6m.Clear()
                        for ($k = $items.Length - $RowBudget; $k -lt $items.Length; $k++) { $t6m.Add($items[$k]) }
                        $t6mMin = [string]$t6m[0][10]
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        if (($mftTotal % 200000) -eq 0) { Say ("      ... " + $mftTotal.ToString("N0") + " MFT rows") }
    }
} finally { $srm.Close() }
Say ("      `$MFT: " + $mftTotal.ToString("N0") + " rows parsed (" + $mftDel.ToString("N0") + " deleted, " +
     $mftStomp.ToString("N0") + " SI<FN, " + $mftIoc.ToString("N0") + " IOC hits)")

# ---------------------------------------------------------------- stage 3: parse + score $J
#  kept-row layout: 0 ts 1 name 2 ext 3 entry 4 seq 5 parentPath 6 updReasons
#                   7 attrs 8 score 9 tags 10 why
$jRows = New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]'
$jTotal = 0; $jIoc = 0
$maxTsJ = ""
$hist = @{}                     # day -> event count (FULL set, pre-reduction)
$creTs = @{}; $delTs = @{}      # entry-seq -> first FileCreate ts / last FileDelete ts
$burst = @{}                    # parentPathLower -> List of row refs with FileCreate

if ($haveJ) {
    Say "[3/6] Parsing + scoring `$J csv ..."
    $srj = New-Object System.IO.StreamReader($jCsv, [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8, $true, 1MB)
    try {
        $hdr = $srj.ReadLine()
        if ($hdr.Length -gt 0 -and [int]$hdr[0] -eq 0xFEFF) { $hdr = $hdr.Substring(1) }
        $map = @{}; $hc = $hdr.Split(','); for ($i = 0; $i -lt $hc.Length; $i++) { $map[$hc[$i]] = $i }
        $cName = ColIx $map "Name";       $cExt = ColIx $map "Extension"
        $cEntry = ColIx $map "EntryNumber"; $cSeq = ColIx $map "SequenceNumber"
        $cPP = ColIx $map "ParentPath";   $cTs = ColIx $map "UpdateTimestamp"
        $cUpd = ColIx $map "UpdateReasons"; $cAttr = ColIx $map "FileAttributes"
        $nCols = $hc.Length

        while ($true) {
            $line = ReadCsvRecord $srj
            if ($null -eq $line) { break }
            if ($line.Length -eq 0) { continue }
            $f = SplitCsvLine $line
            if ($f.Length -lt $nCols) { continue }
            $jTotal++

            $ts = $f[$cTs]; if ($ts.Length -gt 19) { $ts = $ts.Substring(0,19) }
            $fn = $f[$cName]; $pp = $f[$cPP]; $upd = $f[$cUpd]
            $ext = $f[$cExt]; if ($ext.Length -gt 0 -and $ext[0] -eq '.') { $ext = $ext.Substring(1) }
            $extL = $ext.ToLowerInvariant()
            if ($ts.CompareTo($maxTsJ) -gt 0) { $maxTsJ = $ts }
            $day = if ($ts.Length -ge 10) { $ts.Substring(0,10) } else { "?" }
            if ($hist.ContainsKey($day)) { $hist[$day] = $hist[$day] + 1 } else { $hist[$day] = 1 }

            $risky = ($extL.Length -gt 0 -and $RISKYEXT.ContainsKey($extL))
            $isCreate = $upd.IndexOf("FileCreate") -ge 0
            $isDelete = $upd.IndexOf("FileDelete") -ge 0
            $isWrite = $isCreate -or $upd.IndexOf("DataExtend") -ge 0 -or $upd.IndexOf("DataOverwrite") -ge 0 -or $upd.IndexOf("RenameNewName") -ge 0
            $key = $f[$cEntry] + "-" + $f[$cSeq]
            if ($isCreate) {
                if (-not $creTs.ContainsKey($key) -or $ts.CompareTo($creTs[$key]) -lt 0) { $creTs[$key] = $ts }
            }
            if ($isDelete) {
                if (-not $delTs.ContainsKey($key) -or $ts.CompareTo($delTs[$key]) -gt 0) { $delTs[$key] = $ts }
            }

            $score = 0; $tags = ""; $why = ""
            # $J is small enough to lowercase every row; post-passes need $inUser for all
            $fpL = ($pp + "\" + $fn).ToLowerInvariant()
            $inUser = $false
            foreach ($u in $USERPATHS) { if ($fpL.IndexOf($u) -ge 0) { $inUser = $true; break } }
            if ($inUser) {
                foreach ($u in $NOTUSERPATHS) { if ($fpL.IndexOf($u) -ge 0) { $inUser = $false; break } }
            }

            # H1 USERPATH (write/create of risky ext in user-writable path)
            if ($risky -and $inUser -and $isWrite) { $score += 2; $tags += "|USERPATH"; $why += "; risky ext written in user-writable path" }
            # H5 MASQ
            if ($extL -eq "exe") {
                $base = $fn.Substring(0, $fn.Length - 4).ToLowerInvariant()
                if ($OSNAMES.ContainsKey($base) -and $fpL.IndexOf("\windows\") -lt 0) {
                    $score += 3; $tags += "|MASQ"; $why += "; OS binary name outside \Windows"
                }
                # H11 LOLBIN (writes only)
                if ($LOLBINS.ContainsKey($base) -and $inUser -and $isWrite) {
                    $score += 1; $tags += "|LOLBIN"; $why += "; LOLBin written to user-writable path"
                }
            }
            # H6 RANDOM
            if ($risky) {
                $dot = $fn.LastIndexOf('.')
                $base = if ($dot -gt 0) { $fn.Substring(0, $dot).ToLowerInvariant() } else { $fn.ToLowerInvariant() }
                if (LooksRandom $base) { $score += 1; $tags += "|RANDOM"; $why += "; random-looking name" }
            }
            # H7 DBLEXT
            if ($risky -and $reDblExt.IsMatch($fn)) { $score += 2; $tags += "|DBLEXT"; $why += "; double extension" }
            # H10 IOC
            $iocHit = $false
            if ($nIoc -gt 0) {
                $hits = ""
                foreach ($t in $IOCS) {
                    if ($fpL.IndexOf($t) -ge 0) {
                        if ($hits -ne "") { $hits += ", " }
                        $hits += $t
                        if ($hits.Length -gt 120) { break }
                    }
                }
                if ($hits -ne "") { $iocHit = $true; $jIoc++; $score += 5; $tags += "|IOC"; $why += "; IOC hit: " + $hits }
            }

            $entN = 0; [void][int]::TryParse($f[$cEntry], [ref]$entN)
            $seqN = 0; [void][int]::TryParse($f[$cSeq], [ref]$seqN)
            # slots 11-13: internal flags for post-passes (ioc, create, interesting) - stripped at emit
            # risky-ext ONLY: user-path alone would sweep in all AppData cache/temp churn
            $interesting = $risky
            $row = @($ts, $fn, $extL, $entN, $seqN, $pp, $upd, $f[$cAttr], $score,
                     $tags, $why, $(if ($iocHit) {1} else {0}), $(if ($isCreate) {1} else {0}),
                     $(if ($interesting) {1} else {0}))
            $jRows.Add($row)

            if ($isCreate) {
                $ppL = $pp.ToLowerInvariant()
                if (-not $burst.ContainsKey($ppL)) { $burst[$ppL] = New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]' }
                $burst[$ppL].Add($row)
            }
            if (($jTotal % 100000) -eq 0) { Say ("      ... " + $jTotal.ToString("N0") + " USN rows") }
        }
    } finally { $srj.Close() }
    Say ("      `$J: " + $jTotal.ToString("N0") + " rows parsed (" + $jIoc.ToString("N0") + " IOC hits)")

    # ---- post-pass H4 CRTDEL: created AND deleted within window, tag all rows of that entry
    Say "[4/6] Post-passes (CRTDEL, BURST) ..."
    $crtdel = @{}
    $fmt = "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss"
    $ci = [System.Globalization.CultureInfo]::InvariantCulture
    foreach ($k in $creTs.Keys) {
        if ($delTs.ContainsKey($k)) {
            try {
                $c = [datetime]::ParseExact($creTs[$k], $fmt, $ci)
                $d = [datetime]::ParseExact($delTs[$k], $fmt, $ci)
                if ($d -ge $c -and ($d - $c).TotalHours -le $CRTDEL_HOURS) { $crtdel[$k] = $true }
            } catch { }
        }
    }
    # ---- post-pass H8 BURST: >= BURST_N FileCreates in same dir within BURST_SECS
    # epoch-seconds computed once per row; the timestamp format sorts lexicographically
    $burstRows = New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.HashSet[object]'
    $epoch = [datetime]::new(1970,1,1)
    foreach ($ppL in $burst.Keys) {
        $list = $burst[$ppL]
        if ($list.Count -lt $BURST_N) { continue }
        $keys = New-Object 'string[]' $list.Count
        $items = $list.ToArray()
        for ($k = 0; $k -lt $items.Length; $k++) { $keys[$k] = [string]$items[$k][0] }
        [System.Array]::Sort($keys, $items)
        $secs = New-Object 'long[]' $keys.Length
        for ($k = 0; $k -lt $keys.Length; $k++) {
            try { $secs[$k] = [long]([datetime]::ParseExact($keys[$k], $fmt, $ci) - $epoch).TotalSeconds } catch { $secs[$k] = 0 }
        }
        # overlapping windows must not re-add the same items (quadratic otherwise)
        $lo = 0; $marked = -1
        for ($hi = 0; $hi -lt $items.Length; $hi++) {
            while ($lo -lt $hi -and ($secs[$hi] - $secs[$lo]) -gt $BURST_SECS) { $lo++ }
            if (($hi - $lo + 1) -ge $BURST_N) {
                $start = $lo; if ($marked + 1 -gt $start) { $start = $marked + 1 }
                for ($k = $start; $k -le $hi; $k++) { [void]$burstRows.Add($items[$k]) }
                $marked = $hi
            }
        }
    }
    # apply post-pass scores - only to rows that are risky-ext or user-writable-path
    # ("interesting", slot 13); temp/cache churn earns the pattern but not the score
    $nCrt = 0; $nBur = 0
    foreach ($row in $jRows) {
        if ([int]$row[13] -ne 1) { continue }
        $key = ([string]$row[3]) + "-" + ([string]$row[4])
        if ($crtdel.ContainsKey($key)) {
            $row[8] = [int]$row[8] + 2; $row[9] = ([string]$row[9]) + "|CRTDEL"
            $row[10] = ([string]$row[10]) + "; created then deleted within " + $CRTDEL_HOURS + "h"
            $nCrt++
        }
        if ($burstRows.Contains($row)) {
            $row[8] = [int]$row[8] + 1; $row[9] = ([string]$row[9]) + "|BURST"
            $row[10] = ([string]$row[10]) + "; part of a file-creation burst"
            $nBur++
        }
    }
    Say ("      CRTDEL entries: " + $crtdel.Count.ToString("N0") + " (interesting rows tagged " + $nCrt.ToString("N0") + "); BURST rows tagged: " + $nBur.ToString("N0"))
} else {
    Say "[3/6] No `$J supplied - MFT-only report."
    Say "[4/6] (skipped)"
}

# ---------------------------------------------------------------- stage 5: reduce
Say "[5/6] Reducing to row budget ..."

# --- MFT: tiers already split during parse; assemble in priority order
$mftKeep = New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]'
$mftDrop = @{ t1=0; t2=0; t3=0; t4=0; t5=0; t6=0 }
function TakeInto([System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]]$dst, [System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]]$src, [int]$budget, [string]$tier, [hashtable]$dropStats) {
    foreach ($r in $src) {
        if ($dst.Count -lt $budget) { $dst.Add($r) } else { $dropStats[$tier] = $dropStats[$tier] + 1 }
    }
}
TakeInto $mftKeep $t1m $RowBudget "t1" $mftDrop
TakeInto $mftKeep $t2m $RowBudget "t2" $mftDrop
TakeInto $mftKeep $t3m $RowBudget "t3" $mftDrop
TakeInto $mftKeep $t4m $RowBudget "t4" $mftDrop
TakeInto $mftKeep $t5m $RowBudget "t5" $mftDrop
# t6 already bounded; count anything beyond budget as dropped
$t6drop = $mftTotal - $t1m.Count - $t2m.Count - $t3m.Count - $t4m.Count - $t5m.Count - $t6m.Count
if ($t6drop -lt 0) { $t6drop = 0 }
$mftDrop["t6"] = $t6drop
TakeInto $mftKeep $t6m $RowBudget "t6" $mftDrop

# --- J: tier now (post-passes changed scores)
$jKeep = New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]'
$jDrop = @{ t1=0; t2=0; t3=0; t4=0; t5=0; t6=0 }
if ($haveJ) {
    $jt = @{ t1=(New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]'); t2=(New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]');
             t3=(New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]'); t4=(New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]');
             t5=(New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]'); t6=(New-Object 'System.Collections.Generic.List[object[]]') }
    foreach ($row in $jRows) {
        $s = [int]$row[8]
        if ([int]$row[11] -eq 1) { $jt["t1"].Add($row) }
        elseif ($s -ge 4) { $jt["t2"].Add($row) }
        elseif ($s -ge 2) { $jt["t3"].Add($row) }
        elseif ($s -ge 1) { $jt["t4"].Add($row) }
        else {
            $ts = [string]$row[0]
            $inWin = $false
            if ($haveWin) {
                $inWin = $true
                if ($winFrom -ne "" -and $ts.CompareTo($winFrom) -lt 0) { $inWin = $false }
                if ($winTo -ne "" -and $ts.CompareTo($winTo) -gt 0) { $inWin = $false }
            }
            $extL = [string]$row[2]
            if ($inWin -and $extL.Length -gt 0 -and $RISKYEXT.ContainsKey($extL)) { $jt["t5"].Add($row) }
            else { $jt["t6"].Add($row) }
        }
    }
    # newest-first within t6
    $t6j = $jt["t6"]
    if ($t6j.Count -gt 0) {
        $keys = New-Object 'string[]' $t6j.Count
        $items = $t6j.ToArray()
        for ($k = 0; $k -lt $items.Length; $k++) { $keys[$k] = [string]$items[$k][0] }
        [System.Array]::Sort($keys, $items)
        [System.Array]::Reverse($items)
        $t6j.Clear(); foreach ($it in $items) { $t6j.Add($it) }
    }
    TakeInto $jKeep $jt["t1"] $RowBudget "t1" $jDrop
    TakeInto $jKeep $jt["t2"] $RowBudget "t2" $jDrop
    TakeInto $jKeep $jt["t3"] $RowBudget "t3" $jDrop
    TakeInto $jKeep $jt["t4"] $RowBudget "t4" $jDrop
    TakeInto $jKeep $jt["t5"] $RowBudget "t5" $jDrop
    TakeInto $jKeep $jt["t6"] $RowBudget "t6" $jDrop
}

# RECENT tag (context only) on kept rows, anchored to dataset max timestamp
$recentCut = ""
$anchor = $maxTsJ; if ($anchor -eq "" -or ($maxTsM -ne "" -and $maxTsM.CompareTo($anchor) -gt 0)) { $anchor = $maxTsM }
if ($anchor.Length -ge 19) {
    try {
        $a = [datetime]::ParseExact($anchor.Substring(0,19), "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss", [System.Globalization.CultureInfo]::InvariantCulture)
        $recentCut = $a.AddDays(-$RECENT_DAYS).ToString("yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss")
    } catch { }
}
if ($recentCut -ne "") {
    foreach ($r in $mftKeep) { if (([string]$r[10]).CompareTo($recentCut) -ge 0) { $r[15] = (([string]$r[15]) + "|RECENT").TrimStart('|') } }
    foreach ($r in $jKeep)   { if (([string]$r[0]).CompareTo($recentCut) -ge 0)  { $r[9]  = (([string]$r[9])  + "|RECENT").TrimStart('|') } }
}

Say ("      kept MFT " + $mftKeep.Count.ToString("N0") + "/" + $mftTotal.ToString("N0") +
     ", J " + $jKeep.Count.ToString("N0") + "/" + $jTotal.ToString("N0"))

# ---------------------------------------------------------------- stage 6: emit report
Say "[6/6] Emitting report ..."
$sb = New-Object System.Text.StringBuilder (64MB)

[void]$sb.Append('var DATA={')
[void]$sb.Append('"meta":{')
[void]$sb.Append('"host":');       JsonStr $HostLabel $sb
[void]$sb.Append(',"generated":'); JsonStr ([datetime]::UtcNow.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss") + " UTC") $sb
[void]$sb.Append(',"appVersion":'); JsonStr $AppVersion $sb
[void]$sb.Append(',"mftecmdVersion":'); JsonStr $toolVer $sb
[void]$sb.Append(',"mftecmdPath":'); JsonStr $MftecmdPath $sb
[void]$sb.Append(',"inputMft":'); JsonStr $Mft $sb
[void]$sb.Append(',"inputJ":'); JsonStr $J $sb
[void]$sb.Append(',"csvDir":'); JsonStr $csvDir $sb
[void]$sb.Append(',"mftTotal":').Append($mftTotal).Append(',"mftKept":').Append($mftKeep.Count)
[void]$sb.Append(',"jTotal":').Append($jTotal).Append(',"jKept":').Append($jKeep.Count)
[void]$sb.Append(',"mftDeleted":').Append($mftDel).Append(',"mftAds":').Append($mftAds)
[void]$sb.Append(',"mftStomp":').Append($mftStomp).Append(',"iocHits":').Append($mftIoc + $jIoc)
[void]$sb.Append(',"budget":').Append($RowBudget)
[void]$sb.Append(',"recentCut":'); JsonStr $recentCut $sb
[void]$sb.Append(',"winFrom":'); JsonStr $winFrom $sb
[void]$sb.Append(',"winTo":'); JsonStr $winTo $sb
[void]$sb.Append(',"mftDrop":{"t1":').Append($mftDrop.t1).Append(',"t2":').Append($mftDrop.t2).Append(',"t3":').Append($mftDrop.t3)
[void]$sb.Append(',"t4":').Append($mftDrop.t4).Append(',"t5":').Append($mftDrop.t5).Append(',"t6":').Append($mftDrop.t6).Append('}')
[void]$sb.Append(',"jDrop":{"t1":').Append($jDrop.t1).Append(',"t2":').Append($jDrop.t2).Append(',"t3":').Append($jDrop.t3)
[void]$sb.Append(',"t4":').Append($jDrop.t4).Append(',"t5":').Append($jDrop.t5).Append(',"t6":').Append($jDrop.t6).Append('}')
[void]$sb.Append('},')

[void]$sb.Append('"iocs":[')
for ($i = 0; $i -lt $IOCS.Count; $i++) { if ($i -gt 0) { [void]$sb.Append(',') }; JsonStr $IOCS[$i] $sb }
[void]$sb.Append('],')

[void]$sb.Append('"cols":{"mft":["entry","seq","deleted","parentPath","fileName","ext","size","isDir","hasAds","zoneId","cr10","cr30","mod10","acc10","score","tags","why"],')
[void]$sb.Append('"j":["ts","name","ext","entry","seq","parentPath","upd","attrs","score","tags","why"]},')

[void]$sb.Append('"hist":{')
$first = $true
foreach ($day in ($hist.Keys | Sort-Object)) {
    if (-not $first) { [void]$sb.Append(',') }; $first = $false
    JsonStr $day $sb; [void]$sb.Append(':').Append([int]$hist[$day])
}
[void]$sb.Append('},')

[void]$sb.Append('"mft":[')
$first = $true
foreach ($r in $mftKeep) {
    if (-not $first) { [void]$sb.Append(',') }; $first = $false
    [void]$sb.Append('[').Append([int]$r[0]).Append(',').Append([int]$r[1]).Append(',').Append([int]$r[2]).Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[3]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[4]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[5]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    [void]$sb.Append([long]$r[6]).Append(',').Append([int]$r[7]).Append(',').Append([int]$r[8]).Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[9]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[10]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[11]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[12]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[13]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    [void]$sb.Append([int]$r[14]).Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[15]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[16]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(']')
}
[void]$sb.Append('],')

[void]$sb.Append('"j":[')
$first = $true
foreach ($r in $jKeep) {
    if (-not $first) { [void]$sb.Append(',') }; $first = $false
    [void]$sb.Append('[')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[0]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[1]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[2]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    [void]$sb.Append([int]$r[3]).Append(',').Append([int]$r[4]).Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[5]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[6]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[7]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    [void]$sb.Append([int]$r[8]).Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[9]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(',')
    JsonStr ([string]$r[10]) $sb; [void]$sb.Append(']')
}
[void]$sb.Append(']};')
$dataJs = $sb.ToString()

# --- Phase-1 stub viewer. Replaced wholesale by the full viewer in Phase 2.
# [SCRIPT] / [/SCRIPT] tokens are swapped for real script tags at emit time so the
# template can survive later embedding inside the HTA payload block.
$TEMPLATE = @'
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>__TITLE__</title><style>
:root{--bg:#0d1117;--panel:#161b22;--bd:#30363d;--fg:#e6edf3;--mut:#8b949e;--blu:#58a6ff;--red:#ff6b6b;--yel:#d29922;--grn:#3fb950;--pur:#b083f0}
*{box-sizing:border-box}
body{background:var(--bg);color:var(--fg);font-family:"Segoe UI",Tahoma,sans-serif;font-size:14px;margin:0;padding:0}
.mono{font-family:Consolas,"Courier New",monospace}
a{color:var(--blu)}
#hdr{padding:10px 16px 6px 16px}
#hdr h1{font-size:19px;margin:0;display:inline-block}
.pill{display:inline-block;background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--bd);border-radius:12px;padding:1px 10px;margin-left:8px;font-size:12px;color:var(--mut);vertical-align:middle}
.pill b{color:var(--fg)}
#banner{margin:6px 16px;background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--bd);border-left:3px solid var(--yel);border-radius:6px;padding:6px 10px;font-size:12px;color:var(--mut)}
#bar{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center;gap:6px;padding:4px 16px}
.tab{background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--bd);color:var(--fg);border-radius:6px;padding:4px 14px;cursor:pointer;font-size:13px}
.tab.on{background:#1f6feb;border-color:#1f6feb;color:#fff}
button,select,input{background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--bd);color:var(--fg);border-radius:6px;padding:4px 8px;font-size:12px;font-family:inherit}
button{cursor:pointer} button:hover{border-color:var(--blu)}
input[type=text]{width:170px} input.dt{width:98px}
#tagbar{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:4px;padding:4px 16px}
.chip{background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--bd);border-radius:12px;padding:1px 9px;font-size:11.5px;cursor:pointer;color:var(--mut)}
.chip.on{border-color:var(--blu);color:var(--blu)}
.chip.zero{opacity:.35;cursor:default}
.chip b{color:var(--fg);font-weight:600}
#gridwrap{position:relative;margin:2px 16px 8px 16px;border:1px solid var(--bd);border-radius:6px;overflow:auto;background:var(--panel)}
#ghead{position:sticky;top:0;z-index:5;background:#1c2129;display:flex;border-bottom:1px solid var(--bd);min-width:1330px}
#ghead div{padding:5px 8px;font-size:12px;color:var(--mut);cursor:pointer;flex:0 0 auto;overflow:hidden;white-space:nowrap;user-select:none}
#ghead div:hover{color:var(--blu)}
#spacer{position:relative;min-width:1330px}
#rows{position:absolute;left:0;top:0;right:0}
.r{display:flex;height:24px;line-height:23px;font-size:12px;border-bottom:1px solid #1b2028;cursor:pointer;min-width:1330px}
.r:hover{background:#1c2532}
.r div{padding:0 8px;flex:0 0 auto;overflow:hidden;white-space:nowrap;text-overflow:ellipsis}
.r.sus{background:#2a1416}.r.sus:hover{background:#33191c}
.r.sus div:first-child{border-left:3px solid var(--red);padding-left:5px}
.r.sel{outline:1px solid var(--blu)}
.sc{font-weight:700;color:var(--red)}
.tag{display:inline-block;border-radius:4px;padding:0 5px;margin:2px 2px 0 0;font-size:10.5px;line-height:16px;background:#21262d;color:var(--mut);vertical-align:middle}
.tag.IOC,.tag.MASQ{background:#3a1416;color:var(--red);border:1px solid var(--red);line-height:14px}
.tag.IOCX{background:#3a1416;color:#ffa198;border:1px dashed var(--red);line-height:14px}
.tag.USERPATH{background:#3a2d10;color:var(--yel)}
.tag.LOLBIN{background:#10263f;color:var(--blu)}
.tag.RANDOM,.tag.TIMESTOMP{background:#241a3a;color:var(--pur)}
.tag.DBLEXT,.tag.CRTDEL{background:#3a1416;color:var(--red)}
.tag.DELETED{background:#21262d;color:#c9d1d9}
#ov{padding:0 16px 16px 16px;display:none}
.card{background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--bd);border-radius:6px;padding:12px;margin-top:10px}
.card h3{margin:0 0 8px 0;font-size:14px}
.stat{display:inline-block;margin-right:26px;margin-bottom:4px}
.stat b{font-size:19px}.stat span{color:var(--mut);font-size:11.5px;display:block}
.cards3{display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap}
.col3{flex:1 1 300px;background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--bd);border-radius:6px;padding:12px;min-width:300px}
.col3 h3{margin:0 0 8px 0;font-size:13.5px}
.li{font-size:12px;padding:3px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1b2028;cursor:pointer;overflow:hidden;white-space:nowrap;text-overflow:ellipsis}
.li:hover{color:var(--blu)}
.li .muted{color:var(--mut)}
#histo{display:flex;align-items:flex-end;gap:2px;height:110px;padding-top:6px;overflow-x:auto}
.hb{flex:0 0 14px;background:#1f6feb;border-radius:2px 2px 0 0;cursor:pointer;min-height:2px}
.hb:hover{background:var(--blu)}
.hlbl{font-size:10px;color:var(--mut);transform:none;text-align:center}
#detail{position:fixed;top:0;right:-540px;width:520px;height:100%;background:#11151c;border-left:1px solid var(--bd);z-index:50;transition:right .15s;overflow-y:auto;padding:14px;font-size:12.5px}
#detail.open{right:0;box-shadow:-8px 0 24px rgba(0,0,0,.5)}
#detail h2{font-size:15px;margin:0 40px 8px 0;word-break:break-all}
#detail table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;font-size:12px}
#detail td{padding:3px 6px;border-bottom:1px solid #1b2028;vertical-align:top;word-break:break-all}
#detail td:first-child{color:var(--mut);white-space:nowrap;width:110px}
.stomp{color:var(--pur);font-weight:700}
#dx{position:absolute;top:8px;right:10px;font-size:20px;cursor:pointer;color:var(--mut)}#dx:hover{color:var(--fg)}
.dwhy{background:#1c2129;border-radius:6px;padding:8px;margin:8px 0}
.rel{padding:3px 6px;border-bottom:1px solid #1b2028;cursor:pointer;font-size:11.5px;overflow:hidden;white-space:nowrap;text-overflow:ellipsis}
.rel:hover{background:#1c2532}
#iocbox{display:none;padding:6px 16px}
#iocbox textarea{width:60%;height:52px;background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--bd);color:var(--fg);border-radius:6px;font-family:Consolas,monospace;font-size:12px;padding:6px}
.cave{color:var(--yel);font-size:11.5px;margin-left:8px}
#foot{padding:6px 16px 14px 16px;color:var(--mut);font-size:11.5px}
.zone{background:#1c2129;border:1px solid var(--bd);border-radius:6px;padding:6px;font-size:11.5px;word-break:break-all;color:var(--yel)}
#msg{position:fixed;bottom:16px;left:50%;transform:translateX(-50%);background:#1f6feb;color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:6px 16px;font-size:12.5px;display:none;z-index:99}
</style></head><body>
<div id="hdr">
  <h1>__TITLE__</h1>
  <span class="pill" id="pillGen"></span>
  <span class="pill" id="pillVer"></span>
  <span class="pill" id="pillTz"><b>UTC</b> everywhere</span>
</div>
<div id="banner"></div>
<div id="bar">
  <span class="tab on" id="tabOv">Overview</span>
  <span class="tab" id="tabJ">Timeline ($J)</span>
  <span class="tab" id="tabM">Files ($MFT)</span>
  <input type="text" id="q" placeholder="search name / path / tags">
  <input type="text" class="dt mono" id="d1" placeholder="from YYYY-MM-DD">
  <input type="text" class="dt mono" id="d2" placeholder="to YYYY-MM-DD">
  <select id="extq"><option value="">ext: all</option><option>exe</option><option>dll</option><option>sys</option><option>ps1</option><option>bat</option><option>cmd</option><option>vbs</option><option>js</option><option>hta</option><option>jar</option><option>lnk</option><option>7z</option><option>zip</option><option>rar</option><option>iso</option></select>
  <input type="text" id="pscope" placeholder="path contains" style="width:130px">
  <button id="bClear">Clear</button>
  <button id="bIoc">IOC+</button>
  <button id="bCsv">Export CSV</button>
  <button id="bNotes">Copy case notes</button>
  <button id="bFm" title="smaller text">A-</button>
  <button id="bFp" title="larger text">A+</button>
</div>
<div id="iocbox">
  <textarea id="iocTxt" placeholder="ad-hoc terms, comma or newline separated"></textarea>
  <button id="bIocGo" style="vertical-align:top">Apply</button>
  <span class="cave">ad-hoc terms search only the embedded subset; re-run from the launcher to sweep all rows</span>
</div>
<div id="tagbar"></div>
<div id="ov"></div>
<div id="gridwrap" style="display:none">
  <div id="ghead"></div>
  <div id="spacer"><div id="rows"></div></div>
</div>
<div id="detail"><span id="dx">&times;</span><div id="dbody"></div></div>
<div id="foot"></div>
<div id="msg"></div>
[SCRIPT]
/*__DATA__*/
[/SCRIPT]
[SCRIPT]
"use strict";
// ---- column index constants (must match engine emit layout)
var M={E:0,SEQ:1,DEL:2,PP:3,FN:4,EXT:5,SIZE:6,DIR:7,ADS:8,ZONE:9,CR10:10,CR30:11,MOD10:12,ACC10:13,SC:14,TAGS:15,WHY:16};
var J={TS:0,NAME:1,EXT:2,ENT:3,SEQ:4,PP:5,UPD:6,ATTR:7,SC:8,TAGS:9,WHY:10};
var ROWH=24, meta=DATA.meta;
function $(id){return document.getElementById(id)}
function esc(s){return String(s==null?"":s).replace(/&/g,"&amp;").replace(/</g,"&lt;").replace(/>/g,"&gt;").replace(/"/g,"&quot;")}
function nfmt(n){return Number(n).toLocaleString()}
function toast(t){var m=$("msg");m.textContent=t;m.style.display="block";setTimeout(function(){m.style.display="none"},2200)}

// ---- one-time prep: lowercase search blobs + entry index
var mftBlob=new Array(DATA.mft.length), jBlob=new Array(DATA.j.length);
var entryIdx={}; // "entry-seq" -> {m:mftIdx, j:[jIdx]}
(function(){
  var i,r,k;
  for(i=0;i<DATA.mft.length;i++){r=DATA.mft[i];
    mftBlob[i]=(r[M.PP]+"\\"+r[M.FN]+"|"+r[M.EXT]+"|"+r[M.TAGS]+"|"+r[M.WHY]+"|"+r[M.ZONE]).toLowerCase();
    k=r[M.E]+"-"+r[M.SEQ]; if(!entryIdx[k])entryIdx[k]={m:-1,j:[]}; entryIdx[k].m=i;}
  for(i=0;i<DATA.j.length;i++){r=DATA.j[i];
    jBlob[i]=(r[J.PP]+"\\"+r[J.NAME]+"|"+r[J.EXT]+"|"+r[J.TAGS]+"|"+r[J.WHY]+"|"+r[J.UPD]).toLowerCase();
    k=r[J.ENT]+"-"+r[J.SEQ]; if(!entryIdx[k])entryIdx[k]={m:-1,j:[]}; entryIdx[k].j.push(i);}
})();
var adhocM={}, adhocJ={}, adhocOn=false;

// ---- header pills / banner / footer
$("pillGen").innerHTML="generated <b>"+esc(meta.generated)+"</b>";
$("pillVer").innerHTML="engine <b>"+esc(meta.appVersion)+"</b> &middot; MFTECmd <b>"+esc(meta.mftecmdVersion)+"</b>";
(function(){
  var dm=0,dj=0,k;for(k in meta.mftDrop)dm+=meta.mftDrop[k];for(k in meta.jDrop)dj+=meta.jDrop[k];
  $("banner").innerHTML="Showing <b>"+nfmt(meta.mftKept)+"</b> of "+nfmt(meta.mftTotal)+" $MFT rows and <b>"+nfmt(meta.jKept)+"</b> of "+nfmt(meta.jTotal)+
    " $J rows (budget "+nfmt(meta.budget)+"/set; "+nfmt(dm)+" / "+nfmt(dj)+" lowest-priority rows not embedded). "+
    "IOC terms baked at parse time: "+DATA.iocs.length+". Full CSVs: <span class='mono'>"+esc(meta.csvDir)+"</span>";
  $("foot").innerHTML="Host <b>"+esc(meta.host)+"</b> &middot; input "+esc(meta.inputMft)+(meta.inputJ?" + $J":" (no $J)")+
    " &middot; window "+(meta.winFrom?esc(meta.winFrom)+" .. "+esc(meta.winTo):"none")+" &middot; recent-cut "+esc(meta.recentCut)+
    " &middot; all timestamps UTC as emitted by MFTECmd";
})();

// ---- filter state (shared across views)
var VIEW="ov", SORT={j:{k:J.SC,d:-1,k2:J.TS},m:{k:M.SC,d:-1,k2:M.CR10}};
var TAGSEL="ALL";
var filtered=[];   // raw indexes into active dataset
var TAGLIST=["SUS","IOC","IOCX","USERPATH","TIMESTOMP","ADS","DELETED","MASQ","DBLEXT","CRTDEL","BURST","RANDOM","LOLBIN","RECENT"];

function activeRows(){return VIEW==="j"?DATA.j:DATA.mft}
function activeBlob(){return VIEW==="j"?jBlob:mftBlob}
function susOf(r){return VIEW==="j"?r[J.SC]>=2:r[M.SC]>=3}
function tsOf(r){return VIEW==="j"?r[J.TS]:r[M.CR10]}
function tagsOf(r){return VIEW==="j"?r[J.TAGS]:r[M.TAGS]}
function extOf(r){return VIEW==="j"?r[J.EXT]:r[M.EXT]}
function ppOf(r){return VIEW==="j"?r[J.PP]:r[M.PP]}
function adhocSet(){return VIEW==="j"?adhocJ:adhocM}

function hasTag(r,i,t){
  if(t==="ALL")return true;
  if(t==="SUS")return susOf(r);
  if(t==="IOCX")return !!adhocSet()[i];
  return (tagsOf(r)+"").indexOf(t)>=0;
}

function applyFilters(){
  var rows=activeRows(), blob=activeBlob(), out=[], counts={ALL:0};
  var q=$("q").value.trim().toLowerCase();
  var d1=$("d1").value.trim(), d2=$("d2").value.trim();
  if(d1)d1+=" 00:00:00"; if(d2)d2+=" 23:59:59";
  var ext=$("extq").value, ps=$("pscope").value.trim().toLowerCase();
  var i,r,ok,t;
  for(t=0;t<TAGLIST.length;t++)counts[TAGLIST[t]]=0;
  for(i=0;i<rows.length;i++){r=rows[i];
    ok=true;
    if(q&&blob[i].indexOf(q)<0)ok=false;
    if(ok&&d1&&tsOf(r)<d1)ok=false;
    if(ok&&d2&&tsOf(r)>d2)ok=false;
    if(ok&&ext&&extOf(r)!==ext)ok=false;
    if(ok&&ps&&(ppOf(r)+"").toLowerCase().indexOf(ps)<0)ok=false;
    if(!ok)continue;
    counts.ALL++;
    for(t=0;t<TAGLIST.length;t++){if(hasTag(r,i,TAGLIST[t]))counts[TAGLIST[t]]++}
    if(hasTag(r,i,TAGSEL))out.push(i);
  }
  filtered=out;
  sortNow();
  renderTagbar(counts);
  layoutGrid();
}
function sortNow(){
  var rows=activeRows(), s=VIEW==="j"?SORT.j:SORT.m, k=s.k, d=s.d, k2=s.k2;
  filtered.sort(function(a,b){
    var x=rows[a][k], y=rows[b][k];
    if(x<y)return -d; if(x>y)return d;
    x=rows[a][k2]; y=rows[b][k2];
    if(x<y)return 1; if(x>y)return -1; return 0;
  });
}
function renderTagbar(counts){
  var h='<span class="chip'+(TAGSEL==="ALL"?" on":"")+'" data-t="ALL">ALL <b>'+nfmt(counts.ALL)+'</b></span>',t,n;
  for(var i=0;i<TAGLIST.length;i++){t=TAGLIST[i];n=counts[t]||0;
    if(t==="IOCX"&&!adhocOn)continue;
    h+='<span class="chip'+(TAGSEL===t?" on":"")+(n?"":" zero")+'" data-t="'+t+'">'+(t==="IOCX"?"IOC+":t)+' <b>'+nfmt(n)+'</b></span>';}
  $("tagbar").innerHTML=h;
}
$("tagbar").onclick=function(e){
  var t=e.target.closest(".chip"); if(!t)return;
  if(t.classList.contains("zero")&&t.dataset.t!==TAGSEL)return;
  TAGSEL=(TAGSEL===t.dataset.t)?"ALL":t.dataset.t; applyFilters();
};

// ---- grid (virtualized)
var COLS_J=[
 {h:"Score",w:52,g:function(r){return '<span class="sc">'+(r[J.SC]||"")+'</span>'},k:J.SC},
 {h:"Tags",w:180,g:function(r,i){return tagHtml(r[J.TAGS],adhocJ[i])},k:J.SC},
 {h:"Timestamp (UTC)",w:150,g:function(r){return '<span class="mono">'+esc(r[J.TS])+'</span>'},k:J.TS},
 {h:"Name",w:230,g:function(r){return '<span class="mono">'+esc(r[J.NAME])+'</span>'},k:J.NAME},
 {h:"Parent path",w:430,g:function(r){return '<span class="mono">'+esc(r[J.PP])+'</span>'},k:J.PP},
 {h:"Update reasons",w:240,g:function(r){return esc(r[J.UPD])},k:J.UPD},
 {h:"Ext",w:48,g:function(r){return esc(r[J.EXT])},k:J.EXT}];
var COLS_M=[
 {h:"Score",w:52,g:function(r){return '<span class="sc">'+(r[M.SC]||"")+'</span>'},k:M.SC},
 {h:"Tags",w:180,g:function(r,i){return tagHtml(r[M.TAGS],adhocM[i])},k:M.SC},
 {h:"Created 0x10 (UTC)",w:150,g:function(r){return '<span class="mono">'+esc(r[M.CR10])+'</span>'},k:M.CR10},
 {h:"Name",w:230,g:function(r){return '<span class="mono">'+esc(r[M.FN])+'</span>'},k:M.FN},
 {h:"Parent path",w:430,g:function(r){return '<span class="mono">'+esc(r[M.PP])+'</span>'},k:M.PP},
 {h:"Ext",w:48,g:function(r){return esc(r[M.EXT])},k:M.EXT},
 {h:"Size",w:90,g:function(r){return nfmt(r[M.SIZE])},k:M.SIZE},
 {h:"Del",w:40,g:function(r){return r[M.DEL]?"Y":""},k:M.DEL},
 {h:"ADS",w:44,g:function(r){return r[M.ADS]?"Y":""},k:M.ADS}];
function cols(){return VIEW==="j"?COLS_J:COLS_M}
function tagHtml(t,adhoc){
  var o="",a,i; if(t){a=String(t).split("|");
    for(i=0;i<a.length;i++)if(a[i])o+='<span class="tag '+esc(a[i])+'">'+esc(a[i])+'</span>';}
  if(adhoc)o+='<span class="tag IOCX">IOC+</span>';
  return o;
}
var ARR_UP=" "+String.fromCharCode(9650), ARR_DN=" "+String.fromCharCode(9660);
function renderHead(){
  var s=VIEW==="j"?SORT.j:SORT.m, c=cols(), h="",i,arr;
  for(i=0;i<c.length;i++){
    arr=(s.k===c[i].k)?(s.d>0?ARR_UP:ARR_DN):"";
    h+='<div data-k="'+c[i].k+'" style="width:'+c[i].w+'px">'+esc(c[i].h)+arr+'</div>';}
  $("ghead").innerHTML=h;
}
$("ghead").onclick=function(e){
  var t=e.target.closest("div[data-k]"); if(!t)return;
  var s=VIEW==="j"?SORT.j:SORT.m, k=parseInt(t.dataset.k,10);
  if(s.k===k)s.d=-s.d; else {s.k=k;s.d=-1;}
  sortNow(); layoutGrid(); renderHead();
};
var gw=$("gridwrap"), spacer=$("spacer"), rowsEl=$("rows");
function layoutGrid(){
  spacer.style.height=(filtered.length*ROWH)+"px";
  renderWindow(true);
}
var lastFirst=-1;
function renderWindow(force){
  var first=Math.floor(gw.scrollTop/ROWH)-5; if(first<0)first=0;
  if(!force&&first===lastFirst)return;
  lastFirst=first;
  var vis=Math.ceil(gw.clientHeight/ROWH)+10;
  var last=Math.min(filtered.length,first+vis);
  var rows=activeRows(), c=cols(), h="",i,j,r,ri;
  for(i=first;i<last;i++){ri=filtered[i];r=rows[ri];
    h+='<div class="r'+(susOf(r)?" sus":"")+(ri===selIdx?" sel":"")+'" data-ri="'+ri+'">';
    for(j=0;j<c.length;j++)h+='<div style="width:'+c[j].w+'px">'+c[j].g(r,ri)+'</div>';
    h+='</div>';}
  rowsEl.style.top=(first*ROWH)+"px";
  rowsEl.innerHTML=h;
}
var raf=null;
gw.onscroll=function(){if(raf)return;raf=requestAnimationFrame(function(){raf=null;renderWindow(false)})};
window.onresize=function(){sizeGrid();renderWindow(true)};
function sizeGrid(){gw.style.height=Math.max(220,window.innerHeight-gw.getBoundingClientRect().top-46)+"px"}

// ---- detail pane
var selIdx=-1;
rowsEl.onclick=function(e){
  var t=e.target.closest(".r"); if(!t)return;
  openDetail(VIEW,parseInt(t.dataset.ri,10));
};
$("dx").onclick=function(){$("detail").classList.remove("open");selIdx=-1;renderWindow(true)};
document.addEventListener("keydown",function(e){if(e.key==="Escape")$("dx").onclick()});
function openDetail(ds,ri){
  selIdx=(ds===VIEW)?ri:-1;
  var h="";
  if(ds==="j")h=detailJ(ri); else h=detailM(ri);
  $("dbody").innerHTML=h;
  $("detail").classList.add("open");
  renderWindow(true);
  var cb=$("bCopyRec"); if(cb)cb.onclick=function(){copyText(cb.dataset.txt);toast("record copied")};
  var rels=document.querySelectorAll(".rel[data-ds]");
  for(var i=0;i<rels.length;i++)rels[i].onclick=function(){openDetail(this.dataset.ds,parseInt(this.dataset.ri,10))};
}
function trow(k,v,cls){return "<tr><td>"+esc(k)+"</td><td class='"+(cls||"mono")+"'>"+v+"</td></tr>"}
function detailM(ri){
  var r=DATA.mft[ri], key=r[M.E]+"-"+r[M.SEQ], stomp=(r[M.TAGS]+"").indexOf("TIMESTOMP")>=0;
  var h="<h2 class='mono'>"+esc(r[M.PP]+"\\"+r[M.FN])+"</h2>";
  h+="<div>"+tagHtml(r[M.TAGS],adhocM[ri])+" <span class='sc'>score "+r[M.SC]+"</span></div>";
  if(r[M.WHY])h+="<div class='dwhy'>"+esc(r[M.WHY]).replace(/; /g,"<br>")+"</div>";
  h+="<table>";
  h+=trow("Entry-Seq",key);
  h+=trow("Created 0x10",'<span class="'+(stomp?"stomp":"")+'">'+esc(r[M.CR10])+"</span>");
  h+=trow("Created 0x30",'<span class="'+(stomp?"stomp":"")+'">'+esc(r[M.CR30]||"(same as 0x10)")+"</span>");
  h+=trow("Modified 0x10",esc(r[M.MOD10]));
  h+=trow("Accessed 0x10",esc(r[M.ACC10]));
  h+=trow("Size",nfmt(r[M.SIZE]));
  h+=trow("Flags",(r[M.DIR]?"directory ":"")+(r[M.DEL]?"DELETED ":"in use ")+(r[M.ADS]?"has-ADS":""));
  h+="</table>";
  if(r[M.ZONE])h+="<div style='margin-top:8px'><b>Zone.Identifier (download source)</b><div class='zone mono'>"+esc(r[M.ZONE])+"</div></div>";
  h+=relatedHtml(key,"m",ri);
  h+=copyBtn(["MFT record",r[M.PP]+"\\"+r[M.FN],"entry "+key+"  score "+r[M.SC]+"  ["+r[M.TAGS]+"]",
    "cr0x10 "+r[M.CR10]+"  cr0x30 "+(r[M.CR30]||"=")+"  mod "+r[M.MOD10],
    "size "+r[M.SIZE]+(r[M.DEL]?"  DELETED":"")+(r[M.WHY]?"\n"+r[M.WHY]:"")].join("\n"));
  return h;
}
function detailJ(ri){
  var r=DATA.j[ri], key=r[J.ENT]+"-"+r[J.SEQ];
  var h="<h2 class='mono'>"+esc(r[J.PP]+"\\"+r[J.NAME])+"</h2>";
  h+="<div>"+tagHtml(r[J.TAGS],adhocJ[ri])+" <span class='sc'>score "+r[J.SC]+"</span></div>";
  if(r[J.WHY])h+="<div class='dwhy'>"+esc(r[J.WHY]).replace(/; /g,"<br>")+"</div>";
  h+="<table>";
  h+=trow("Timestamp",esc(r[J.TS]));
  h+=trow("Entry-Seq",key);
  h+=trow("Update reasons",esc(r[J.UPD]),"");
  h+=trow("Attributes",esc(r[J.ATTR]),"");
  h+="</table>";
  h+=relatedHtml(key,"j",ri);
  h+=copyBtn(["USN event",r[J.PP]+"\\"+r[J.NAME],"entry "+key+"  score "+r[J.SC]+"  ["+r[J.TAGS]+"]",
    r[J.TS]+"  "+r[J.UPD]+(r[J.WHY]?"\n"+r[J.WHY]:"")].join("\n"));
  return h;
}
function relatedHtml(key,self,selfRi){
  var e=entryIdx[key], h="", i, r;
  if(!e)return h;
  h+="<div style='margin-top:10px'><b>Story of entry "+esc(key)+"</b></div>";
  if(e.m>=0){r=DATA.mft[e.m];
    if(!(self==="m"&&e.m===selfRi))
      h+="<div class='rel mono' data-ds='m' data-ri='"+e.m+"'>MFT: "+esc(r[M.FN])+"  cr "+esc(r[M.CR10])+(r[M.DEL]?"  DELETED":"")+"  score "+r[M.SC]+"</div>";
  } else if(self==="j") h+="<div class='rel' style='cursor:default;color:#8b949e'>MFT record not in embedded set (deleted+recycled or below budget)</div>";
  if(e.j.length){
    var cap=Math.min(e.j.length,120);
    for(i=0;i<cap;i++){if(self==="j"&&e.j[i]===selfRi)continue;r=DATA.j[e.j[i]];
      h+="<div class='rel mono' data-ds='j' data-ri='"+e.j[i]+"'>"+esc(r[J.TS])+"  "+esc(r[J.UPD])+"</div>";}
    if(e.j.length>cap)h+="<div class='rel' style='cursor:default;color:#8b949e'>("+(e.j.length-cap)+" more events)</div>";
  } else if(self==="m") h+="<div class='rel' style='cursor:default;color:#8b949e'>no embedded $J events for this entry (journal window or budget)</div>";
  return h;
}
function copyBtn(txt){return "<div style='margin-top:12px'><button id='bCopyRec' data-txt=\""+esc(txt)+"\">Copy record</button></div>"}
function copyText(t){
  var ta=document.createElement("textarea");ta.value=t;document.body.appendChild(ta);
  ta.select();try{document.execCommand("copy")}catch(e){}document.body.removeChild(ta);
}

// ---- overview
function renderOverview(){
  var h="",i,r;
  h+="<div class='card'>"
   +"<div class='stat'><b>"+nfmt(meta.mftTotal)+"</b><span>MFT records</span></div>"
   +"<div class='stat'><b>"+nfmt(meta.jTotal)+"</b><span>USN events</span></div>"
   +"<div class='stat'><b>"+nfmt(meta.mftDeleted)+"</b><span>deleted files</span></div>"
   +"<div class='stat'><b>"+nfmt(meta.mftStomp)+"</b><span>SI&lt;FN flagged</span></div>"
   +"<div class='stat'><b>"+nfmt(meta.mftAds)+"</b><span>with ADS</span></div>"
   +"<div class='stat'><b>"+nfmt(meta.iocHits)+"</b><span>IOC hits</span></div>"
   +"<div class='stat'><b>"+nfmt(meta.mftKept)+" / "+nfmt(meta.jKept)+"</b><span>embedded MFT / $J</span></div>"
   +"</div>";
  // histogram (full $J set, computed pre-reduction)
  var days=Object.keys(DATA.hist).sort(), max=1;
  for(i=0;i<days.length;i++)if(DATA.hist[days[i]]>max)max=DATA.hist[days[i]];
  if(days.length){
    h+="<div class='card'><h3>$J activity by day (full journal, "+nfmt(meta.jTotal)+" events) &mdash; click a bar to open that day in Timeline</h3><div id='histo'>";
    for(i=0;i<days.length;i++){
      var pct=Math.max(2,Math.round(DATA.hist[days[i]]/max*100));
      h+="<div style='text-align:center'><div class='hb' data-day='"+esc(days[i])+"' style='height:"+pct+"px' title='"+esc(days[i])+": "+nfmt(DATA.hist[days[i]])+" events'></div><div class='hlbl'>"+esc(days[i].substring(5))+"</div></div>";}
    h+="</div></div>";
  }
  // 3-col dashboard
  var topM=[],topX=[],dirs={},dl=[];
  var idx=[];for(i=0;i<DATA.mft.length;i++)idx.push(i);
  idx.sort(function(a,b){var x=DATA.mft[a],y=DATA.mft[b];if(y[M.SC]!==x[M.SC])return y[M.SC]-x[M.SC];return y[M.CR10]<x[M.CR10]?-1:1});
  for(i=0;i<idx.length&&topM.length<12;i++){r=DATA.mft[idx[i]];if(r[M.SC]>=3)topM.push(idx[i]);else break}
  for(i=0;i<idx.length&&topX.length<12;i++){r=DATA.mft[idx[i]];if(r[M.EXT]==="exe"||r[M.EXT]==="dll"||r[M.EXT]==="sys")topX.push(idx[i])}
  topX.sort(function(a,b){return DATA.mft[b][M.CR10]<DATA.mft[a][M.CR10]?-1:1});topX=topX.slice(0,12);
  for(i=0;i<DATA.j.length;i++){r=DATA.j[i];if((r[J.UPD]+"").indexOf("FileCreate")>=0){dirs[r[J.PP]]=(dirs[r[J.PP]]||0)+1}}
  for(var d in dirs)dl.push([d,dirs[d]]); dl.sort(function(a,b){return b[1]-a[1]}); dl=dl.slice(0,12);
  h+="<div class='cards3'>";
  h+="<div class='col3'><h3>Top suspicious MFT records</h3>";
  if(!topM.length)h+="<div class='li' style='cursor:default'>none at score &gt;= 3</div>";
  for(i=0;i<topM.length;i++){r=DATA.mft[topM[i]];
    h+="<div class='li mono' data-ds='m' data-ri='"+topM[i]+"' title='"+esc(r[M.PP]+"\\"+r[M.FN])+"'><span class='sc'>"+r[M.SC]+"</span> "+esc(r[M.FN])+" <span class='muted'>"+esc(r[M.CR10])+"</span></div>";}
  h+="</div>";
  h+="<div class='col3'><h3>Busiest dirs by file-creates <span class='muted'>(embedded $J)</span></h3>";
  for(i=0;i<dl.length;i++)h+="<div class='li mono' data-dir=\""+esc(dl[i][0])+"\" title='"+esc(dl[i][0])+"'>"+nfmt(dl[i][1])+"  "+esc(dl[i][0])+"</div>";
  h+="</div>";
  h+="<div class='col3'><h3>Newest executables (exe/dll/sys)</h3>";
  for(i=0;i<topX.length;i++){r=DATA.mft[topX[i]];
    h+="<div class='li mono' data-ds='m' data-ri='"+topX[i]+"' title='"+esc(r[M.PP]+"\\"+r[M.FN])+"'>"+esc(r[M.CR10])+" <span class='muted'>"+esc(r[M.FN])+"</span></div>";}
  h+="</div></div>";
  $("ov").innerHTML=h;
  var lis=document.querySelectorAll("#ov .li[data-ds]");
  for(i=0;i<lis.length;i++)lis[i].onclick=function(){openDetail(this.dataset.ds,parseInt(this.dataset.ri,10))};
  lis=document.querySelectorAll("#ov .li[data-dir]");
  for(i=0;i<lis.length;i++)lis[i].onclick=function(){setView("j");$("pscope").value=this.dataset.dir;applyFilters()};
  var hbs=document.querySelectorAll("#ov .hb");
  for(i=0;i<hbs.length;i++)hbs[i].onclick=function(){$("d1").value=this.dataset.day;$("d2").value=this.dataset.day;setView("j")};
}

// ---- view switching
function setView(v){
  VIEW=v;
  $("tabOv").className="tab"+(v==="ov"?" on":"");
  $("tabJ").className="tab"+(v==="j"?" on":"");
  $("tabM").className="tab"+(v==="m"?" on":"");
  $("ov").style.display=(v==="ov")?"block":"none";
  $("gridwrap").style.display=(v==="ov")?"none":"block";
  $("tagbar").style.display=(v==="ov")?"none":"flex";
  if(v==="ov"){renderOverview();return}
  if(v==="j"&&!DATA.j.length){toast("no $J data in this report")}
  renderHead(); sizeGrid(); gw.scrollTop=0; lastFirst=-1; applyFilters();
}
$("tabOv").onclick=function(){setView("ov")};
$("tabJ").onclick=function(){setView("j")};
$("tabM").onclick=function(){setView("m")};

// ---- filter inputs
var deb=null;
function refire(){if(VIEW==="ov")return;if(deb)clearTimeout(deb);deb=setTimeout(applyFilters,200)}
$("q").oninput=refire; $("d1").oninput=refire; $("d2").oninput=refire;
$("extq").onchange=function(){if(VIEW!=="ov")applyFilters()};
$("pscope").oninput=refire;
$("bClear").onclick=function(){$("q").value="";$("d1").value="";$("d2").value="";$("extq").value="";$("pscope").value="";TAGSEL="ALL";if(VIEW!=="ov")applyFilters()};

// ---- ad-hoc IOC
$("bIoc").onclick=function(){var b=$("iocbox");b.style.display=(b.style.display==="block")?"none":"block"};
$("bIocGo").onclick=function(){
  var terms=$("iocTxt").value.split(/[,\r\n]+/).map(function(s){return s.trim().toLowerCase()}).filter(function(s){return s&&s.charAt(0)!=="#"});
  adhocM={};adhocJ={};adhocOn=terms.length>0;
  var i,t,hit;
  if(adhocOn){
    for(i=0;i<mftBlob.length;i++){hit=false;for(t=0;t<terms.length;t++)if(mftBlob[i].indexOf(terms[t])>=0){hit=true;break}if(hit)adhocM[i]=1}
    for(i=0;i<jBlob.length;i++){hit=false;for(t=0;t<terms.length;t++)if(jBlob[i].indexOf(terms[t])>=0){hit=true;break}if(hit)adhocJ[i]=1}
  }
  var nm=Object.keys(adhocM).length,nj=Object.keys(adhocJ).length;
  toast("IOC+ matched "+nfmt(nm)+" MFT / "+nfmt(nj)+" $J embedded rows");
  if(VIEW==="ov")renderOverview();else applyFilters();
};

// ---- export / case notes
$("bCsv").onclick=function(){
  if(VIEW==="ov"){toast("switch to Timeline or Files first");return}
  var rows=activeRows(),c=cols(),i,j,r,line,out=[],hd=[];
  var names=VIEW==="j"?DATA.cols.j:DATA.cols.mft;
  out.push(names.join(","));
  for(i=0;i<filtered.length;i++){r=rows[filtered[i]];line=[];
    for(j=0;j<r.length;j++){var v=String(r[j]==null?"":r[j]);
      line.push(/[",\n]/.test(v)?'"'+v.replace(/"/g,'""')+'"':v)}
    out.push(line.join(","))}
  var blob=new Blob([out.join("\r\n")],{type:"text/csv"});
  var a=document.createElement("a");a.href=URL.createObjectURL(blob);
  a.download=meta.host+"-"+(VIEW==="j"?"USN":"MFT")+"-filtered.csv";a.click();
  toast("exported "+nfmt(filtered.length)+" rows");
};
$("bNotes").onclick=function(){
  var L=[],i,r;
  L.push("MFT/USN triage - "+meta.host+" (generated "+meta.generated+", engine "+meta.appVersion+")");
  L.push("Parsed "+nfmt(meta.mftTotal)+" $MFT rows / "+nfmt(meta.jTotal)+" $J rows; "+nfmt(meta.iocHits)+" IOC hits; "+nfmt(meta.mftStomp)+" SI<FN flagged; "+nfmt(meta.mftDeleted)+" deleted.");
  L.push("Embedded "+nfmt(meta.mftKept)+"/"+nfmt(meta.jKept)+" (budget "+nfmt(meta.budget)+"). All times UTC.");
  L.push("");
  var idx=[];for(i=0;i<DATA.mft.length;i++)if(DATA.mft[i][M.SC]>=3)idx.push(i);
  idx.sort(function(a,b){return DATA.mft[b][M.SC]-DATA.mft[a][M.SC]});
  L.push("Top suspicious MFT records ("+nfmt(idx.length)+" at score >= 3):");
  for(i=0;i<Math.min(idx.length,10);i++){r=DATA.mft[idx[i]];
    L.push("  ["+r[M.SC]+"] "+r[M.CR10]+"  "+r[M.PP]+"\\"+r[M.FN]+"  ("+r[M.TAGS]+")")}
  idx=[];for(i=0;i<DATA.j.length;i++)if(DATA.j[i][J.SC]>=2)idx.push(i);
  idx.sort(function(a,b){return DATA.j[b][J.SC]-DATA.j[a][J.SC]});
  L.push("Top suspicious USN events ("+nfmt(idx.length)+" at score >= 2):");
  for(i=0;i<Math.min(idx.length,10);i++){r=DATA.j[idx[i]];
    L.push("  ["+r[J.SC]+"] "+r[J.TS]+"  "+r[J.PP]+"\\"+r[J.NAME]+"  ("+r[J.UPD]+")")}
  copyText(L.join("\n"));toast("case notes copied");
};

// ---- font size (zoom scales layout uniformly; virtualization math is unaffected)
var ZOOM=1;
$("bFm").onclick=function(){ZOOM=Math.max(0.7,Math.round((ZOOM-0.1)*10)/10);document.body.style.zoom=ZOOM;if(VIEW!=="ov"){sizeGrid();renderWindow(true)}};
$("bFp").onclick=function(){ZOOM=Math.min(1.4,Math.round((ZOOM+0.1)*10)/10);document.body.style.zoom=ZOOM;if(VIEW!=="ov"){sizeGrid();renderWindow(true)}};

// ---- boot
setView("ov");
[/SCRIPT]
</body></html>
'@

# build the close-script tag by concatenation so the literal sequence never appears
# in this PS1 source - lets the whole engine embed inside the HTA payload block unharmed
$openTag = "<script>"; $closeTag = "<" + "/scr" + "ipt>"
$html = $TEMPLATE.Replace("[SCRIPT]", $openTag).Replace("[/SCRIPT]", $closeTag)
$html = $html.Replace("__TITLE__", ($safeHost + " - MFT/USN Triage Report"))
$html = $html.Replace("/*__DATA__*/", $dataJs)

$reportPath = Join-Path $OutDir ($safeHost + "-MFT-Report.html")
[System.IO.File]::WriteAllText($reportPath, $html, (New-Object System.Text.UTF8Encoding($false)))

Say ("Done in " + $sw.Elapsed.ToString("mm\:ss") + " - report " +
     ("{0:N1}" -f ((Get-Item -LiteralPath $reportPath).Length / 1MB)) + " MB")
Write-Output $reportPath
exit 0
# MFTECMD-ENGINE-END
</script>

<script language="JScript">
"use strict";

var APP_VERSION = "1.1.1";
var KNOWN_LATEST_MFTECMD = "2026.5.0";                                            // baseline as of 2026-07-03 (current EZ .NET9 CalVer build; KAPE bundled an older 1.2.2.1)
var MFTECMD_ZIP_URL = "https://download.ericzimmermanstools.com/net9/MFTECmd.zip";  // official EZ mirror (.NET 9 build)
var MFTECMD_PAGE = "https://ericzimmerman.github.io/";                            // live latest-version lookup
var EXE = "", EXE_DIR = "", LOCAL_VER = "", LATEST_VER = "", WEB_OK = false;
var BUSY = false;
var LAST_REPORT = "";
var ENGINE_PS1 = "";                 // resolved path of the extracted engine on disk

/* ---------- tiny helpers ---------- */
function $(id){ return document.getElementById(id); }
function esc(s){ if(s==null) return ""; s=String(s);
  return s.replace(/&/g,"&amp;").replace(/</g,"&lt;").replace(/>/g,"&gt;").replace(/"/g,"&quot;"); }
function trimStr(s){ return String(s).replace(/^\s+|\s+$/g,""); }
function setStatus(msg,cls){ var el=$("status"); el.innerHTML=esc(msg); el.className=cls||"muted"; }
function appendLog(t){ var el=$("log"); if(el.getAttribute("data-ph")==="1"){ el.innerHTML=""; el.setAttribute("data-ph","0"); }
  el.style.display="block"; $("logToggle").innerHTML="Hide log"; el.innerHTML+=esc(t)+"\n"; el.scrollTop=el.scrollHeight; }
function setLog(t){ var el=$("log"); el.setAttribute("data-ph","0"); el.style.display="block"; $("logToggle").innerHTML="Hide log";
  el.innerHTML=esc(t); el.scrollTop=el.scrollHeight; }
function uid(){ return new Date().getTime()+""+Math.floor(Math.random()*100000); }
function fileExists(p){ try{ return new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject").FileExists(p); }catch(e){ return false; } }
function folderExists(p){ try{ return new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject").FolderExists(p); }catch(e){ return false; } }
function parentDir(p){ var i=String(p).lastIndexOf("\\"); return i>=0?p.substring(0,i):p; }
function baseName(p){ if(!p) return ""; p=String(p); var i=Math.max(p.lastIndexOf("\\"),p.lastIndexOf("/")); return i>=0?p.substring(i+1):p; }
/* cmd expands %VAR% inside .bat FILE lines even in quotes - double them there only */
function batEsc(s){ return String(s).replace(/%/g,"%%"); }

/* ---------- file IO with network-zone fallback (ADODB -> FSO), from the family ---------- */
var FILE_IO="adodb";
function zoneNote(){ appendLog("NOTE: Windows security-zone policy is blocking the UTF-8 file reader (ADODB.Stream). Usual cause is that this .hta was DOWNLOADED (it carries a Mark-of-the-Web) or sits on a network path - not the C: location itself. Falling back to ANSI file IO for the small helper files (IOC list, log); the engine and report are unaffected and processing works normally. To clear it: right-click the .hta > Properties > tick Unblock, or run  Unblock-File '<path to .hta>'  in PowerShell, then reopen."); }
function writeText(path,text){
  if(FILE_IO==="adodb"){
    try{ var st=new ActiveXObject("ADODB.Stream"); st.Type=2; st.Charset="utf-8"; st.Open(); st.WriteText(text); st.SaveToFile(path,2); st.Close(); return; }
    catch(e){ if(!/safety settings|data source/i.test(e.message||"")) throw e; FILE_IO="fso"; zoneNote(); }
  }
  var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject"); var f=fso.CreateTextFile(path,true,false); f.Write(text); f.Close();
}
function readText(path){
  if(FILE_IO==="adodb"){
    try{ var st=new ActiveXObject("ADODB.Stream"); st.Type=2; st.Charset="utf-8"; st.Open(); st.LoadFromFile(path);
      var parts=[]; while(!st.EOS){ parts.push(st.ReadText(65536)); } st.Close(); return parts.join(""); }
    catch(e){ if(!/safety settings|data source/i.test(e.message||"")) throw e; FILE_IO="fso"; zoneNote(); }
  }
  var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject"); var f=fso.OpenTextFile(path,1,false,0), out=f.ReadAll(); f.Close();
  if(out.length>=3 && out.charCodeAt(0)===239 && out.charCodeAt(1)===187 && out.charCodeAt(2)===191) out=out.substring(3);
  return out;
}
/* the PS1 payload is pure ASCII - write it with FSO (ANSI) which is exactly right and zone-immune */
function writeAscii(path,text){ var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject"); var f=fso.CreateTextFile(path,true,false); f.Write(text); f.Close(); }

/* ---------- async batch runner (family runBatAsync/pollDone) ---------- */
function runBatAsync(lines, show){
  var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject");
  var sh=new ActiveXObject("WScript.Shell");
  var tmp=fso.GetSpecialFolder(2)+"";
  var stamp=uid();
  var bat=tmp+"\\mftw_"+stamp+".bat";
  var logp=tmp+"\\mftw_"+stamp+".log";
  var donep=tmp+"\\mftw_"+stamp+".done";
  var f=fso.CreateTextFile(bat,true);
  f.WriteLine("@echo off");
  for(var i=0;i<lines.length;i++){ f.WriteLine(lines[i].replace(/__LOG__/g,logp)); }
  f.WriteLine('echo done> "'+donep+'"');
  f.Close();
  sh.Run('cmd /c ""'+bat+'""', show?1:0, false);
  return { bat:bat, log:logp, done:donep, elapsed:0 };
}
function runBatSync(lines, show){
  var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject");
  var sh=new ActiveXObject("WScript.Shell");
  var tmp=fso.GetSpecialFolder(2)+"", stamp=uid();
  var bat=tmp+"\\mftw_"+stamp+".bat", logp=tmp+"\\mftw_"+stamp+".log";
  var f=fso.CreateTextFile(bat,true); f.WriteLine("@echo off");
  for(var i=0;i<lines.length;i++){ f.WriteLine(lines[i].replace(/__LOG__/g,logp)); }
  f.Close();
  var rc=sh.Run('cmd /c ""'+bat+'""', show?1:0, true);
  var txt=""; try{ if(fso.FileExists(logp)) txt=readText(logp); }catch(e){ txt="(log unreadable: "+e.message+")"; }
  try{ fso.DeleteFile(bat); }catch(e2){}
  try{ if(fso.FileExists(logp)) fso.DeleteFile(logp); }catch(e3){}
  return { rc:rc, log:txt };
}
function pollDone(ctx){
  if(ctx.finished) return;
  var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject");
  // stream the growing log into the pane each tick
  try{ if(fso.FileExists(ctx.log)) setLog(readText(ctx.log)); }catch(eLog){}

  var done=false; try{ if(fso.FileExists(ctx.done)) done=true; }catch(eD){}

  // Robust secondary signal: the engine writes the report as its FINAL action. If the
  // report for THIS run (modified at/after start) exists and its size has stopped
  // growing, the run finished even when the temp .done marker was missed - e.g. the
  // console window was closed, or a Bastion/remote-session poll hiccup dropped it.
  var stable=false;
  if(!done && ctx.report){
    try{
      if(fso.FileExists(ctx.report)){
        var f=fso.GetFile(ctx.report), mt=0;
        try{ mt=(new Date(f.DateLastModified)).getTime(); }catch(_m){}
        if(mt>=ctx.startMs-3000){                 // this run's report, not a stale one
          var sz=f.Size;
          if(sz>0 && sz===ctx.lastSize){ ctx.stableCount++; } else { ctx.stableCount=0; }
          ctx.lastSize=sz;
          if(ctx.stableCount>=3) stable=true;      // ~3s unchanged => write finished
        }
      }
    }catch(eR){}
  }

  if(done||stable){
    ctx.finished=true;
    var log=""; try{ if(fso.FileExists(ctx.log)) log=readText(ctx.log); }catch(e){ log="(log unreadable: "+e.message+")"; }
    try{ fso.DeleteFile(ctx.bat); }catch(e1){}
    try{ if(fso.FileExists(ctx.done)) fso.DeleteFile(ctx.done); }catch(e2){}
    try{ if(fso.FileExists(ctx.log)) fso.DeleteFile(ctx.log); }catch(e3){}
    ctx.onDone(log, (stable&&!done)?"stable":"marker");
    return;
  }
  ctx.elapsed+=1;
  if(ctx.elapsed>2400){ ctx.onTimeout&&ctx.onTimeout(); return; }   // 40-min cap (MFT parse can be minutes)
  if(ctx.onTick) ctx.onTick(ctx.elapsed);
  window.setTimeout(function(){ pollDone(ctx); }, 1000);
}

/* ---------- app folder / payload extraction ---------- */
function htaFolder(){
  try{ var cl=mftHta.commandLine+""; var m=cl.match(/"([^"]+\.hta)"/i); if(!m) m=cl.match(/([A-Za-z]:\\[^"]+\.hta)/i);
    if(m) return parentDir(m[1]); }catch(e){}
  try{ var p=decodeURIComponent(location.pathname+"").replace(/^\//,"").replace(/\//g,"\\"); return parentDir(p); }catch(e2){}
  return "";
}
function isNetworkPath(p){
  try{ if(/^\\\\/.test(p)) return true;
    var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject");
    return fso.GetDrive(fso.GetDriveName(p)).DriveType===3; }catch(e){ return false; }
}
function payloadText(){
  var el=$("ps1Payload"); var t=(el.text!=null?el.text:el.innerHTML)+"";
  // strip a single leading newline introduced by the block formatting
  t=t.replace(/^\r?\n/,"");
  return t;
}
function payloadOK(t){ return t.indexOf("# MFTECMD-ENGINE-START")>=0 && t.indexOf("# MFTECMD-ENGINE-END")>=0; }
/* extract the engine next to the .hta (overwrite always); fall back to %TEMP% on a read-only share */
function extractEngine(){
  var t=payloadText();
  if(!payloadOK(t)){ setStatus("Embedded engine payload is missing or corrupt (self-check failed). Re-splice MFTECmd-Engine.ps1 into this .hta.","err"); return ""; }
  var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject");
  var dir=htaFolder(), targets=[];
  if(dir) targets.push(dir+"\\MFTECmd-Engine.ps1");
  targets.push(fso.GetSpecialFolder(2)+"\\MFTECmd-Engine.ps1");
  for(var i=0;i<targets.length;i++){
    try{ writeAscii(targets[i], t);
      // verify round-trip
      var back=readText(targets[i]);
      if(payloadOK(back)){ if(i>0) appendLog("App folder not writable - engine extracted to TEMP: "+targets[i]); return targets[i]; }
    }catch(e){ /* try next target */ }
  }
  setStatus("Could not write the engine PS1 to the app folder or TEMP.","err");
  return "";
}

/* ---------- MFTECmd discovery / version / download ---------- */
function resolveExe(){
  var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject");
  var dir=htaFolder(), cands=[];
  if(dir) cands.push(dir+"\\MFTECmd.exe");
  cands.push("C:\\Users\\Forensics\\Downloads\\1-Package\\KAPE\\Modules\\bin\\MFTECmd.exe");   // known install on this box
  cands.push("C:\\ZimmermanTools\\net9\\MFTECmd.exe");
  cands.push("C:\\ZimmermanTools\\MFTECmd.exe");
  cands.push("C:\\Tools\\net9\\MFTECmd.exe");
  for(var i=0;i<cands.length;i++){ if(fso.FileExists(cands[i])){ EXE=cands[i]; EXE_DIR=parentDir(cands[i]); return true; } }
  EXE=""; EXE_DIR=dir||""; return false;
}
function verTuple(v){ var p=String(v).split("."); var a=[]; for(var i=0;i<p.length;i++) a.push(parseInt(p[i],10)||0); return a; }
function verCmp(a,b){ a=verTuple(a); b=verTuple(b); var n=Math.max(a.length,b.length);
  for(var i=0;i<n;i++){ var x=a[i]||0,y=b[i]||0; if(x!==y) return x<y?-1:1; } return 0; }
function fetchLatest(){
  LATEST_VER=KNOWN_LATEST_MFTECMD; WEB_OK=false;
  try{ var x=new ActiveXObject("MSXML2.ServerXMLHTTP.6.0"); x.setTimeouts(2000,3000,4000,4000);
    x.open("GET", MFTECMD_PAGE, false); x.send();
    if(x.status===200){ WEB_OK=true; var t=x.responseText+""; var m=t.match(/MFTECmd[\s\S]{0,800}?(\d+\.\d+\.\d+(?:\.\d+)?)/i); if(m) LATEST_VER=m[1]; }
  }catch(e){ WEB_OK=false; }
  return LATEST_VER;
}
function updateVerPill(){
  var s=LOCAL_VER?("MFTECmd v"+esc(LOCAL_VER)):"MFTECmd: not found";
  if(!WEB_OK){ s+=" &middot; <span style='color:#8b949e'>no web check</span>"; }
  else if(LATEST_VER){
    if(LOCAL_VER && verCmp(LOCAL_VER,LATEST_VER)<0) s+=" &middot; <span style='color:#d29922'>v"+esc(LATEST_VER)+" available</span>";
    else if(LOCAL_VER) s+=" &middot; <span style='color:#3fb950'>latest</span>";
    else s+=" &middot; latest v"+esc(LATEST_VER);
  }
  $("verpill").innerHTML=s;
}
function checkVersion(){
  if(!EXE || !fileExists(EXE)){ LOCAL_VER=""; updateVerPill(); setStatus("MFTECmd.exe not found - use 'Update / download MFTECmd'","err"); return; }
  try{
    var r=runBatSync(["set DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD=Major", '"'+batEsc(EXE)+'" --version > "__LOG__" 2>&1']);
    // current EZ builds print a bare CalVer semver "2026.5.0+<githash>"; older
    // builds print "MFTECmd version 1.2.2.1". Match a 3- or 4-part version, stop at '+'.
    var m=r.log.match(/MFTECmd version (\d+\.\d+\.\d+(?:\.\d+)?)/i);
    if(!m) m=r.log.match(/(\d+\.\d+\.\d+(?:\.\d+)?)/);
    if(m){ LOCAL_VER=m[1]; updateVerPill(); setStatus("MFTECmd v"+LOCAL_VER+" detected","ok"); }
    else { LOCAL_VER=""; updateVerPill(); setStatus("Ran MFTECmd but could not parse version - see log","err"); appendLog(r.log); }
  }catch(e){ LOCAL_VER=""; updateVerPill(); setStatus("Version check failed: "+e.message,"err"); }
}
function evaluateTooling(){
  var dir=htaFolder();
  var found=resolveExe();
  if(EXE) $("exeline").innerHTML="MFTECmd: "+esc(EXE)+"  &middot;  run with DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD=Major";
  else $("exeline").innerHTML='<span class="err">MFTECmd.exe not found next to this app or in the known locations - use Update / download</span>';
  if(found) checkVersion(); else LOCAL_VER="";
  fetchLatest(); updateVerPill();
}
function downloadLatest(){
  var target=htaFolder()||EXE_DIR;
  if(!target){ setStatus("Cannot determine the app folder to install into","err"); return; }
  if(!confirm("Download MFTECmd (.NET 9 build) from:\n"+MFTECMD_ZIP_URL+"\n\nInstall next to this app into:\n"+target+"\n\nProceed?")) return;
  setStatus("Downloading & installing MFTECmd…","muted");
  var tq=String(target).replace(/'/g,"''");
  var ps="$ErrorActionPreference='Stop';"
    +"[Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol=[Net.SecurityProtocolType]::Tls12;"
    +"$u='"+MFTECMD_ZIP_URL+"';"
    +"$z=Join-Path $env:TEMP 'MFTECmd_dl.zip';"
    +"$x=Join-Path $env:TEMP ('MFTECmd_x_'+[guid]::NewGuid().ToString('N'));"
    +"Invoke-WebRequest -Uri $u -OutFile $z;"
    +"Expand-Archive -Force -Path $z -DestinationPath $x;"
    +"$exe=Get-ChildItem -Path $x -Recurse -Filter MFTECmd.exe | Select-Object -First 1;"
    +"if(-not $exe){throw 'MFTECmd.exe not found in downloaded archive'};"
    +"$src=Split-Path $exe.FullName;"
    +"New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path '"+tq+"' | Out-Null;"
    +"Copy-Item -Path (Join-Path $src '*') -Destination '"+tq+"' -Recurse -Force;"
    +"Remove-Item $z,$x -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue;"
    +"Write-Output 'INSTALL_OK'";
  try{
    var r=runBatSync(['powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Command "'+ps+'" > "__LOG__" 2>&1']);
    appendLog("--- MFTECmd download / install ---\n"+r.log);
    if((r.log+"").indexOf("INSTALL_OK")>=0){ setStatus("MFTECmd installed to "+target,"ok"); evaluateTooling(); }
    else setStatus("Download/install failed - see log","err");
  }catch(e){ setStatus("Download failed: "+e.message,"err"); }
}

/* ---------- input guessing ---------- */
/* given a chosen $MFT, look for a sibling $J in the same NTFS root (Velociraptor layout) */
function guessJ(mft){
  if(!mft) return "";
  var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject");
  var root=parentDir(mft);
  var cands=[
    root+"\\$Extend\\$UsnJrnl%3A$J",
    root+"\\$Extend\\$UsnJrnl$J",
    root+"\\$Extend\\$J",
    root+"\\$J"
  ];
  for(var i=0;i<cands.length;i++){ try{ if(fso.FileExists(cands[i])) return cands[i]; }catch(e){} }
  return "";
}
/* pull a hostname-ish token out of a Velociraptor collection path */
function guessHost(p){
  if(!p) return "";
  var m=String(p).match(/Collection-([A-Za-z0-9][A-Za-z0-9\-_]+?)-\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}/);
  if(m) return m[1];
  return "";
}
/* recursively find $MFT under a collection root (bounded) */
var MFT_MAX=12, MFT_DEPTH_MAX=24, MFT_SCAN_MAX=40000, MFT_DIRS=0;
function findMfts(root){
  var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject"), out=[]; MFT_DIRS=0;
  function walk(fld,depth){
    if(out.length>=MFT_MAX||depth>MFT_DEPTH_MAX||MFT_DIRS>=MFT_SCAN_MAX) return;
    MFT_DIRS++;
    try{ var fe=new Enumerator(fld.Files);
      for(;!fe.atEnd();fe.moveNext()){ var f=fe.item();
        if(String(f.Name).toUpperCase()==="$MFT"){ out.push(f.Path+""); if(out.length>=MFT_MAX) return; } } }catch(e1){}
    try{ var de=new Enumerator(fld.SubFolders);
      for(;!de.atEnd();de.moveNext()){ walk(de.item(),depth+1); if(out.length>=MFT_MAX) return; } }catch(e2){}
  }
  try{ walk(fso.GetFolder(root),0); }catch(e){}
  return out;
}

/* ---------- the run ---------- */
function processRun(){
  if(BUSY){ setStatus("A run is already in progress.","err"); return; }
  var mft=trimStr($("mftPath").value);
  if(!mft || !fileExists(mft)){ setStatus("Pick a valid $MFT file first.","err"); return; }
  var j=trimStr($("jPath").value);
  if(j && !fileExists(j)){ setStatus("The $J path is set but does not exist - clear it or fix it.","err"); return; }
  if(!EXE || !fileExists(EXE)){ setStatus("MFTECmd.exe not found - use 'Update / download MFTECmd'.","err"); return; }

  var outDir=trimStr($("outDir").value);
  if(!outDir){ setStatus("Set an output folder.","err"); return; }
  var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject");
  try{ if(!fso.FolderExists(outDir)) fso.CreateFolder(outDir); }catch(e){ setStatus("Cannot create output folder: "+e.message,"err"); return; }

  ENGINE_PS1=extractEngine();
  if(!ENGINE_PS1) return;

  var host=trimStr($("hostLabel").value)||guessHost(mft)||"HOST";
  var budget=$("rowBudget").value;
  var wf=trimStr($("winFrom").value), wt=trimStr($("winTo").value);

  // the engine writes <OutDir>\<safeHost>-MFT-Report.html as its FINAL step; pollDone
  // watches for that as a robust completion signal. safeHost must match the engine's own
  // sanitization ([^A-Za-z0-9-_.] -> _). Delete any stale copy so we only detect this run's.
  var safeHost = host.replace(/[^A-Za-z0-9\-_.]/g,"_");
  var expectedReport = outDir.replace(/[\\\/]+$/,"") + "\\" + safeHost + "-MFT-Report.html";
  try{ if(fso.FileExists(expectedReport)) fso.DeleteFile(expectedReport); }catch(eDel){}

  // IOC list -> temp file (avoids command-line quoting/length limits)
  var iocFile="";
  var iocs=trimStr($("iocBox").value);
  if(iocs){ iocFile=fso.GetSpecialFolder(2)+"\\mft_iocs_"+uid()+".txt"; try{ writeText(iocFile, iocs); }catch(e2){ appendLog("Could not write IOC temp file: "+e2.message); iocFile=""; } }

  // build the PS invocation. Engine args are passed as -File params (single-% paths).
  var q=function(s){ return '"'+String(s).replace(/"/g,'\\"')+'"'; };
  var psArgs="-NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File "+q(ENGINE_PS1)
    +" -Mft "+q(mft)
    +(j?(" -J "+q(j)):"")
    +" -OutDir "+q(outDir)
    +" -HostLabel "+q(host)
    +(iocFile?(" -IocFile "+q(iocFile)):"")
    +" -RowBudget "+budget
    +(wf?(" -From "+q(wf)):"")
    +(wt?(" -To "+q(wt)):"")
    +" -AppVersion "+q(APP_VERSION)
    +" -MftecmdPath "+q(EXE);

  BUSY=true; $("runBtn").disabled=true; $("viewBtn").disabled=true;
  setStatus("Running MFTECmd + engine… a console window shows live progress.","muted");
  appendLog("=== MFTECmd Wrapper run "+(new Date())+" ===");
  appendLog("engine: "+ENGINE_PS1);
  appendLog("host="+host+"  budget="+budget+"  $J="+(j?"yes":"no")+"  iocs="+(iocFile?"yes":"none"));

  // batEsc only the wrapping .bat line (the powershell command line itself is a bat line)
  var ctx=runBatAsync([ "powershell "+batEsc(psArgs)+" > \"__LOG__\" 2>&1" ], true);
  ctx.onTick=function(s){ setStatus("Working… "+s+"s (MFT parse is the slow part; large volumes take a few minutes)","muted"); };
  ctx.onTimeout=function(){ BUSY=false; $("runBtn").disabled=false; setStatus("Engine still running after 40 min - check the console window.","err"); };
  ctx.onDone=function(lg, mode){
    BUSY=false; $("runBtn").disabled=false;
    // engine prints the report path on its LAST non-empty line; fall back to the
    // expected <OutDir>\<host>-MFT-Report.html if the log was truncated (process killed).
    var rep=""; var lines=(lg+"").replace(/\r/g,"").split("\n");
    for(var i=lines.length-1;i>=0;i--){ var ln=trimStr(lines[i]); if(ln){ if(/\.html$/i.test(ln)) rep=ln; break; } }
    if((!rep || !fileExists(rep)) && fileExists(expectedReport)) rep=expectedReport;
    if(!rep || !fileExists(rep)){
      setStatus(/ERROR:/.test(lg)?"Run failed - see log.":"Run finished but no report file was found - see log.","err");
      appendLog("--- last engine output ---\n"+tailLines(lg,30));
      return;
    }
    if(mode==="stable") appendLog("(completion detected from the finished report file; the temp done-marker was not seen - harmless.)");
    LAST_REPORT=rep; $("viewBtn").disabled=false;
    if(iocFile){ try{ fso.DeleteFile(iocFile); }catch(e3){} }
    setStatus("Report ready: "+rep,"ok");
    appendLog("Report: "+rep);
    openReport(rep);
  };
  // START the completion poll. This kickoff was missing in <=1.0.1: the run completed
  // on disk but the UI never noticed (button stayed disabled, no auto-open). pollDone
  // now watches BOTH the temp .done marker AND the finished report file (size-stable).
  ctx.report=expectedReport; ctx.startMs=(new Date()).getTime();
  ctx.stableCount=0; ctx.lastSize=-1; ctx.finished=false;
  window.setTimeout(function(){ pollDone(ctx); }, 1000);
}
function tailLines(s,n){ var a=(s+"").replace(/\r/g,"").split("\n"); if(a.length<=n) return s; return a.slice(a.length-n).join("\n"); }

/* open the report in Edge; fall back to the default browser */
function openReport(rep){
  var sh=new ActiveXObject("WScript.Shell");
  try{ sh.Run('msedge.exe "'+rep+'"', 1, false); return; }catch(e){}
  try{ sh.Run('cmd /c start "" "msedge.exe" "'+rep+'"', 0, false); return; }catch(e2){}
  try{ sh.Run('"'+rep+'"', 1, false); }catch(e3){ setStatus("Could not open the report automatically: "+rep,"err"); }
}

/* ---------- browse dialogs ---------- */
function browseFolder(prompt){
  try{ var sha=new ActiveXObject("Shell.Application");
    var fld=sha.BrowseForFolder(0, prompt, 0x51);
    if(fld){ var p=""; try{ p=fld.Self.Path+""; }catch(e2){}
      if(/^[a-z]:\\|^\\\\/i.test(p)) return p; } }catch(e){}
  return "";
}

/* ---------- init / wireup ---------- */
function init(){
  try{ window.resizeTo(1000,820); }catch(e){}
  $("appver").innerHTML="&middot; v"+APP_VERSION;
  try{ document.title="MFTECmd Wrapper v"+APP_VERSION; }catch(e){}

  // startup self-check on the payload
  var pt=payloadText();
  if(!payloadOK(pt)){ setStatus("WARNING: embedded engine payload failed its self-check - re-splice MFTECmd-Engine.ps1 before running.","err"); }
  else { $("modepill").innerHTML="engine embedded ("+Math.round(pt.length/1024)+" KB)"; }

  // default output folder next to the .hta
  var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject");
  var base=htaFolder()||fso.GetSpecialFolder(2)+"";
  var outDir=base+"\\MFT Reports";
  try{ if(!fso.FolderExists(outDir)) fso.CreateFolder(outDir); }catch(e){}
  $("outDir").value=outDir;

  var zoom=0.9;
  var zContent=$("content");
  function applyZoom(){ zContent.style.zoom=zoom; var p=Math.round(zoom*100)+"%";
    $("fup").title="Larger text ("+p+")"; $("fdown").title="Smaller text ("+p+")"; }
  applyZoom();
  $("fup").onclick=function(){ zoom=Math.min(zoom+0.15,2.5); applyZoom(); };
  $("fdown").onclick=function(){ zoom=Math.max(zoom-0.15,0.6); applyZoom(); };

  // hidden native file pickers
  $("mftBrowse").onclick=function(){ $("mftPick").click(); };
  $("mftPick").onchange=function(){ if(this.value){ $("mftPath").value=this.value;
    var g=guessJ(this.value); if(g && !trimStr($("jPath").value)){ $("jPath").value=g; setStatus("Found a sibling $J and filled it in.","ok"); }
    var h=guessHost(this.value); if(h && !trimStr($("hostLabel").value)) $("hostLabel").value=h; } };
  $("jBrowse").onclick=function(){ $("jPick").click(); };
  $("jPick").onchange=function(){ if(this.value) $("jPath").value=this.value; };
  $("jClear").onclick=function(){ $("jPath").value=""; };

  $("mftDirBrowse").onclick=function(){
    var p=browseFolder("Select a collection folder - it is searched recursively for $MFT.");
    if(!p){ setStatus("No folder chosen (or it has no filesystem path).","muted"); return; }
    setStatus("Searching "+p+" for $MFT…","muted");
    window.setTimeout(function(){
      var hits=findMfts(p);
      if(!hits.length){ setStatus("No $MFT found under "+p,"err"); return; }
      // prefer the largest (the system volume); fill the first, report count
      $("mftPath").value=hits[0];
      var g=guessJ(hits[0]); if(g) $("jPath").value=g;
      var h=guessHost(hits[0]); if(h) $("hostLabel").value=h;
      setStatus("Found "+hits.length+" $MFT - using "+hits[0]+(hits.length>1?" (edit the path if you meant another)":""),"ok");
    },30);
  };

  $("iocLoad").onclick=function(){ $("iocPick").click(); };
  $("iocPick").onchange=function(){ if(this.value){ try{ $("iocBox").value=readText(this.value); }catch(e){ setStatus("Could not read IOC file: "+e.message,"err"); } } };

  $("outBrowse").onclick=function(){ var p=browseFolder("Select an output folder for the report and CSVs."); if(p) $("outDir").value=p; };
  $("outOpen").onclick=function(){ var d=trimStr($("outDir").value); if(d && folderExists(d)){ try{ new ActiveXObject("WScript.Shell").Run('explorer.exe "'+d+'"',1,false); }catch(e){} } };

  $("runBtn").onclick=processRun;
  $("viewBtn").onclick=function(){ if(LAST_REPORT && fileExists(LAST_REPORT)) openReport(LAST_REPORT); };
  $("verBtn").onclick=checkVersion;
  $("updBtn").onclick=downloadLatest;
  $("logToggle").onclick=function(){ var l=$("log");
    if(l.style.display==="none"||!l.style.display){ l.style.display="block"; this.innerHTML="Hide log"; }
    else { l.style.display="none"; this.innerHTML="Show log"; } };

  var __cli=parseCli(); try{ applyCli(__cli); }catch(eC){ appendLog("CLI parse error: "+eC.message); }
  evaluateTooling();
  if(isNetworkPath(htaFolder()))
    appendLog("Heads-up: running from a network location ("+htaFolder()+"). The engine extracts locally-first then falls back to %TEMP%; small helper-file IO falls back to ANSI automatically.");
}
/* ---------- command-line invocation: "<inputOrReport>" ["<outDir>"] [/auto] ----------
   .htm/.html → open an existing report; a $MFT file or a collection directory → prefill (+build if /auto).
   Lets an external artifact-finder open the analyzer already pointed at a $MFT (or re-open a prior report). */
/* HTA:APPLICATION.commandLine is UNDEFINED in IE=edge document mode (a known mshta quirk that silently
   kills CLI args). Recover it from WMI: the newest mshta.exe process whose command line names this .hta. */
function getCommandLine(){
  try{ var cl=mftHta.commandLine+""; if(cl && cl!=="undefined") return cl; }catch(e){}
  try{
    var lp=decodeURIComponent(location.pathname+"").replace(/^\//,"").replace(/\//g,"\\");
    var fn=lp.substring(lp.lastIndexOf("\\")+1).toLowerCase(); if(!fn) return "";
    var loc=new ActiveXObject("WbemScripting.SWbemLocator"), svc=loc.ConnectServer(".","root\\cimv2");
    var q=svc.ExecQuery("SELECT CommandLine,CreationDate FROM Win32_Process WHERE Name='mshta.exe'");
    var best="", bestDate="", en=new Enumerator(q);
    for(; !en.atEnd(); en.moveNext()){ var pr=en.item(); var pcl=(pr.CommandLine==null?"":pr.CommandLine+"");
      if(pcl.toLowerCase().indexOf(fn)<0) continue; var cd=(pr.CreationDate==null?"":pr.CreationDate+"");
      if(!best || cd>bestDate){ best=pcl; bestDate=cd; } }
    return best;
  }catch(e2){}
  return "";
}
function tokenizeCmdTail(){ var cl=getCommandLine(); if(!cl) return [];
  var m=cl.match(/\.hta"?/i); var tail=m?cl.substring(m.index+m[0].length):cl;
  var toks=[],i=0,n=tail.length,cur="",inq=false;
  while(i<n){ var c=tail.charAt(i);
    if(inq){ if(c==='"'){inq=false;} else cur+=c; i++; continue; }
    if(c==='"'){ inq=true; i++; continue; }
    if(c===' '||c==='\t'){ if(cur!==""){toks.push(cur);cur="";} i++; continue; }
    cur+=c; i++; }
  if(cur!=="") toks.push(cur); return toks; }
function parseCli(){ var toks=tokenizeCmdTail(), cli={input:"",outDir:"",auto:false};
  for(var i=0;i<toks.length;i++){ var t=toks[i];
    if(/^[\/\-]{1,2}auto$/i.test(t)){ cli.auto=true; continue; }
    if(/^[\/\-]/.test(t)) continue;
    if(!cli.input) cli.input=t; else if(!cli.outDir) cli.outDir=t; }
  return cli; }
function applyCli(cli){ if(!cli.input) return false;
  var fso=new ActiveXObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject");
  if(/\.html?$/i.test(cli.input) && fso.FileExists(cli.input)){ appendLog("CLI: opening report "+cli.input); LAST_REPORT=cli.input; window.setTimeout(function(){ openReport(cli.input); },60); return true; }
  if(fso.FolderExists(cli.input)){ var hits=findMfts(cli.input);
    if(!hits.length){ setStatus("CLI: no $MFT found under "+cli.input,"err"); appendLog("CLI: no $MFT under "+cli.input); return false; }
    $("mftPath").value=hits[0]; var g=guessJ(hits[0]); if(g) $("jPath").value=g; var h=guessHost(hits[0]); if(h) $("hostLabel").value=h; }
  else if(fso.FileExists(cli.input)){ $("mftPath").value=cli.input; var g2=guessJ(cli.input); if(g2) $("jPath").value=g2; var h2=guessHost(cli.input); if(h2) $("hostLabel").value=h2; }
  else { setStatus("CLI input not found: "+cli.input,"err"); appendLog("CLI input not found: "+cli.input); return false; }
  if(cli.outDir) $("outDir").value=cli.outDir;
  if(cli.auto){ appendLog("CLI: /auto — building report for "+cli.input); window.setTimeout(function(){ processRun(); },200); }
  else setStatus("CLI: $MFT prefilled — click Run to build the report.","muted");
  return true; }

/* ---------- help / about overlay ---------- */
var GITHUB="https://github.com/bpmorris22/MFTECmd-Wrapper";
function openUrl(u){ try{ new ActiveXObject("WScript.Shell").Run('"'+u+'"',1,false); }catch(e){ setStatus("Could not open browser: "+e.message,"err"); } }
function openHelp(){ try{ $("helpVer").innerHTML="v"+APP_VERSION; }catch(e){} var m=$("helpModal"); m.className=m.className.replace(/\s*\bhide\b/g,""); }
function closeHelp(){ var m=$("helpModal"); if(!/\bhide\b/.test(m.className)) m.className+=" hide"; }

window.onload=init;
</script>

<input type="file" id="mftPick" class="hide">
<input type="file" id="jPick" class="hide">
<input type="file" id="iocPick" class="hide">

<div id="helpModal" class="modal hide" onclick="if((event.srcElement||{}).id==='helpModal')closeHelp()">
  <div class="mcard">
    <span class="x" onclick="closeHelp()" title="Close">&times;</span>
    <h2>MFTECmd Wrapper <span class="muted" style="font-size:13px;font-weight:400" id="helpVer"></span></h2>
    <div class="gh muted">GitHub: <span class="lnk" onclick="openUrl(GITHUB)">https://github.com/bpmorris22/MFTECmd-Wrapper</span></div>
    <p>A single-file launcher that parses the <b>$MFT</b> (and optional <b>$J</b>) with Eric Zimmerman's MFTECmd and builds a self-contained, virtualized-grid <b>HTML timeline report</b> that opens in your browser.</p>
    <h3>Quick start</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Put this <code>.hta</code> next to <code>MFTECmd.exe</code>, or use the update/download button to fetch it.</li>
      <li>Browse to a <code>$MFT</code> (a sibling <code>$J</code> and host name are auto-detected) or a collection folder, set the host label, then <b>Run</b> — the report builds and opens automatically.</li>
      <li><b>View report</b> re-opens the last report; the report is offline and safe to archive in the case folder.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Command line</h3>
    <p><code>mshta "MFTECmd-Wrapper.hta" "&lt;inputOrReport&gt;" ["&lt;outDir&gt;"] [/auto]</code></p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>&lt;input&gt;</code> — a <code>$MFT</code> file / collection directory (prefilled; report built with <code>/auto</code>), or an existing <code>.html</code> report to re-open.</li>
      <li><code>&lt;outDir&gt;</code> — output directory for the report &amp; CSVs (optional). &nbsp; <code>/auto</code> — build immediately.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Notes</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>The launcher needs Windows <code>mshta.exe</code>; the report needs only a modern browser (Edge/Chrome) and is fully self-contained. An IOC/keyword list is built in.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted" style="font-size:11px">MIT © 2026 Ben Morris — click the link above for the full README &amp; releases.</p>
  </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>
